WEBVTT

01:24.250 --> 01:30.840
[shouting inaudibly]

01:41.893 --> 01:46.689
[dogs barking]

02:01.788 --> 02:03.289
[Klaus] <i>Katie!</i>

02:04.499 --> 02:05.917
<i>Cora!</i>

02:06.292 --> 02:07.961
[whispering] <i>You love your sister?</i>

02:08.044 --> 02:09.212
<i>You make any noise, you know what happens.</i>

02:09.462 --> 02:10.672
[gasps]

02:12.924 --> 02:14.926
[man speaking indistinctly on radio]

02:30.400 --> 02:32.026
[turns radio off]

02:33.778 --> 02:35.864
-[water running]
-[grunts]

02:57.051 --> 02:58.720
Good morning, Estelle.

02:58.803 --> 03:01.681
-[old man] How am I looking, Paul?
-That's better. That's better.

03:06.477 --> 03:08.479
[indistinct conversations]

03:18.448 --> 03:20.575
[Hector] Morning, Mr. Edgecomb.

03:20.658 --> 03:21.951
Some Danish this morning?

03:22.035 --> 03:25.204
No, just two pieces of dry toast, Hector.
Thanks.

03:25.288 --> 03:26.873
Leftover's fine.

03:26.956 --> 03:28.666
Dry and cold, same as always.

03:29.417 --> 03:30.418
Cold is better.

03:31.002 --> 03:32.086
Hmm.

03:32.170 --> 03:33.880
Especially on those long walks.

03:35.506 --> 03:36.591
Am I right?

03:38.301 --> 03:41.221
Don't let Nurse Godzilla catch you.
She'll raise holy hell.

03:41.804 --> 03:43.848
You know we're not supposed
to let you wander off.

03:46.935 --> 03:50.939
Where do you go, every day?
What do you do up in those hills?

03:51.689 --> 03:53.024
Just walk.

03:53.775 --> 03:55.318
I like to walk.

03:57.904 --> 03:59.864
You try not to fall down, bust a hip.

04:00.490 --> 04:03.284
I don't wanna be in no damn search party.

04:05.203 --> 04:06.996
[indistinct shouting]

04:23.429 --> 04:25.098
[thunder rumbling]

05:12.770 --> 05:15.398
[woman 1 on TV] <i>What? Do you want</i>
<i>this man constantly in your life?</i>

05:15.481 --> 05:17.275
<i>Explain the moral basis of that.</i>

05:17.358 --> 05:18.359
[woman 2] <i>I admit I've made mistakes.</i>

05:18.443 --> 05:20.028
<i>Tony doesn't admit that</i>
<i>he's not a good father.</i>

05:20.111 --> 05:22.363
<i>No, it's not...</i>
<i>She can't ask nothin', okay?</i>

05:22.447 --> 05:23.406
<i>You can't ask nothin'.</i>

05:23.489 --> 05:24.782
<i>-I had six kids myself.</i>
-[all laughing]

05:26.659 --> 05:28.536
Why do we always watch this stuff?

05:29.412 --> 05:30.788
It's interesting.

05:31.956 --> 05:33.249
Interesting?

05:33.333 --> 05:35.585
Bunch of inbred trailer trash?

05:36.461 --> 05:38.463
All they ever talk about is fucking.

05:39.130 --> 05:41.007
[woman 1] <i>It ain't no way</i>
<i>in this God green earth</i>

05:41.090 --> 05:42.633
<i>I'm gonna have a father like that!</i>

05:42.717 --> 05:44.802
<i>-If what you say is true...</i>
-[woman speaking indistinctly]

05:44.886 --> 05:46.220
[woman 1] <i>No, I'm talking now!</i>

05:46.304 --> 05:47.597
<i>I'm talking now!</i>

05:47.680 --> 05:48.848
<i>What kind of a mother are you?</i>

05:49.140 --> 05:50.558
[woman 3] <i>One that</i>
<i>causes people more than...</i>

05:50.641 --> 05:53.186
[man 1] <i>...is going</i>
<i>to let you try the Body Strider...</i>

05:53.269 --> 05:55.313
<i>You're dead! You can't come back!</i>

05:55.396 --> 05:58.399
[man 2] <i>It's back.</i>
<i>The Popeil Pocket Fisherman.</i>

05:58.775 --> 06:01.027
[woman 4] <i>All right, all right.</i>
<i>Take my husband, take my kids...</i>

06:01.110 --> 06:02.945
Are you all right?

06:03.029 --> 06:04.072
Hmm?

06:04.155 --> 06:06.699
You look tired. You're not yourself.

06:06.783 --> 06:09.118
No, I'm... I'm fine. I promise.
[chuckles]

06:09.827 --> 06:12.121
You're wearing yourself out
with those walks every day,

06:12.205 --> 06:13.664
that's what I think.

06:13.748 --> 06:15.625
Not that you asked me.

06:15.958 --> 06:18.336
I just didn't sleep well, is all.

06:19.837 --> 06:22.632
I had a few bad dreams. It happens. It...

06:23.424 --> 06:24.884
I'll be fine.

06:25.426 --> 06:26.511
<i>What do you think of that?</i>

06:26.594 --> 06:29.347
[all singing]

06:33.684 --> 06:34.560
[soft music playing]

06:34.644 --> 06:36.312
<i>Oh, if Madge doesn't care,</i>
<i>I certainly don't.</i>

06:36.395 --> 06:38.272
<i>Neither do I. All I know is...</i>

06:38.356 --> 06:40.316
Now, this here is worth a look.

06:40.399 --> 06:42.193
[man singing on TV]

07:23.025 --> 07:24.360
[sniffles]

07:25.903 --> 07:27.196
Paul, what is it?

07:27.405 --> 07:28.698
[sobbing]

07:29.574 --> 07:30.783
My God.

07:36.581 --> 07:38.583
I've got to get out of here.

07:46.382 --> 07:47.967
[rain pattering]

07:49.427 --> 07:51.179
[lightning cracking]

08:00.688 --> 08:04.150
I guess sometimes the past
just catches up with you

08:04.233 --> 08:07.111
whether you want it to or not. It's silly.

08:07.820 --> 08:11.115
Was it the film? It was, wasn't it?

08:12.533 --> 08:16.078
I haven't spoken of these things
for a long time, Ellie.

08:16.996 --> 08:18.372
Over 60 years.

08:18.706 --> 08:20.875
Paul, I'm your friend.

08:26.047 --> 08:30.092
I ever tell you that I was a prison guard
during the Depression?

08:30.176 --> 08:31.677
Uh, you've mentioned it.

08:32.637 --> 08:35.348
Did I mention that
I was in charge of death row,

08:35.431 --> 08:37.558
that I supervised all the executions?

08:42.188 --> 08:45.900
Usually, death row is called
"The Last Mile."

08:47.068 --> 08:49.403
We called ours "The Green Mile."

08:50.154 --> 08:52.823
The floor was the color of faded limes.

08:54.158 --> 08:56.160
We had the electric chair.

08:57.161 --> 08:58.955
"Old Sparky," we called it.

09:01.374 --> 09:03.084
Oh, I've lived a lot of years, Ellie.

09:03.167 --> 09:06.295
But, [clicks tongue] 1935,

09:06.379 --> 09:08.172
that takes the prize.

09:10.174 --> 09:12.134
That year, I had

09:12.218 --> 09:15.221
the worst urinary infection
of my life and...

09:17.306 --> 09:18.641
It was...

09:19.684 --> 09:21.727
It was also the year

09:22.520 --> 09:23.854
of John Coffey and

09:25.898 --> 09:27.775
the two dead girls.

09:28.901 --> 09:29.819
[prisoners singing]

09:29.902 --> 09:30.820
<i>Old Alabama</i>

09:30.903 --> 09:35.199
<i>J'ines the state of Floridy</i>

09:35.533 --> 09:37.034
[horn blowing]

09:38.828 --> 09:44.500
<i>At Mobile, lordy, at Mobile</i>

09:48.462 --> 09:54.677
<i>Old Alabama is a hog killing country</i>

09:57.305 --> 09:58.556
[braying]

10:01.601 --> 10:08.107
<i>Old Alabama is a hog killing country</i>

10:11.360 --> 10:15.031
<i>Every fall, lordy, every fall</i>

10:15.114 --> 10:16.532
[honks horn]

10:22.788 --> 10:25.082
[man 1] All right, now, hold on!

10:29.795 --> 10:32.506
[guard] Up on the tower!
New prisoners coming in!

10:32.590 --> 10:34.592
You men down in the yard,
step off the fence! Clear that gate!

10:34.675 --> 10:36.302
[whistle blowing]

10:41.349 --> 10:42.600
[ringing]

10:43.309 --> 10:44.727
Put me through to E Block.

10:50.733 --> 10:52.276
[phone ringing]

10:58.866 --> 11:00.076
E Block.

11:00.660 --> 11:01.744
Yeah.

11:02.453 --> 11:03.621
Right.

11:16.634 --> 11:17.676
Oh.

11:23.641 --> 11:24.725
[sighs]

11:24.809 --> 11:26.811
[Brutal] Paul? Prisoner.

11:27.269 --> 11:28.771
Christ, give me a minute.

11:33.442 --> 11:34.485
[Paul grunts]

11:34.568 --> 11:35.653
You all right in there?

11:36.070 --> 11:37.405
[grunting]

11:38.447 --> 11:41.909
For a man pissing razor blades, yeah.

11:41.992 --> 11:43.160
[inhales sharply] Ah!

11:46.414 --> 11:48.499
-[toilet flushes]
-[Paul] Oh.

11:56.841 --> 11:59.009
You should've took the day off,
gone to see the doctor.

11:59.677 --> 12:02.221
With a new arrival? You know better.

12:02.596 --> 12:04.265
Besides... [sighs]

12:04.807 --> 12:08.102
It's not as bad as it was.
I think it's clearing up.

12:09.770 --> 12:11.230
[car horn honks]

12:11.313 --> 12:13.107
-All right. Let's look alive, Dean.
-Yes, sir.

12:13.566 --> 12:15.067
[horn honking]

12:20.573 --> 12:21.657
Damn.

12:23.117 --> 12:25.202
They're riding on the axle.

12:34.670 --> 12:36.213
What'd they do?

12:36.839 --> 12:38.090
They bust the springs?

12:41.343 --> 12:42.344
[rattling]

12:43.429 --> 12:44.638
Holy...

12:46.849 --> 12:48.142
Dead man!

12:49.185 --> 12:50.853
Dead man walking!

12:51.520 --> 12:53.647
-Who...
-[Percy] We got a dead man walking here!

12:55.524 --> 12:57.943
Jesus, please us,
what is he yelling about?

13:00.821 --> 13:01.906
Paul,

13:03.032 --> 13:06.160
you might wanna reconsider
getting in the cell with this guy.

13:06.243 --> 13:07.828
He's enormous.

13:07.912 --> 13:09.914
Can't be bigger than you.

13:10.539 --> 13:11.790
[exhales]

13:12.666 --> 13:14.001
[chuckles]

13:15.628 --> 13:16.962
[Percy] Dead man walking.

13:20.299 --> 13:21.884
Dead man!

13:22.301 --> 13:23.928
Dead man walking!

13:24.178 --> 13:25.429
Dead man!

13:26.096 --> 13:27.348
Dead man walking!

13:28.390 --> 13:30.267
Dead man walking here!

13:31.894 --> 13:33.145
Dead man!

13:36.732 --> 13:38.567
We got a dead man walking here!

13:40.236 --> 13:41.445
Dead man walking!

13:43.822 --> 13:46.825
-We got a dead man walking here!
-[Paul] Percy.

13:47.618 --> 13:48.994
That's enough.

14:12.226 --> 14:14.603
Am I gonna have any trouble
with you, big boy?

14:19.733 --> 14:20.776
Can you talk?

14:24.572 --> 14:25.781
[gasps]

14:26.949 --> 14:29.785
[stutters] Yes, sir, boss. I can talk.

14:39.044 --> 14:41.505
-Move your ass. Let's go.
-[tapping stick]

14:42.006 --> 14:43.257
Come on.

14:48.554 --> 14:49.555
Percy,

14:51.265 --> 14:53.475
they're moving house
down in the infirmary.

14:54.310 --> 14:57.271
Why don't you go see
if they could use some help?

14:58.105 --> 14:59.648
No. They got all the men they need.

15:00.399 --> 15:01.984
Why don't you just go and make sure?

15:04.069 --> 15:06.113
-Uh-uh.
-I don't care where you go, Percy,

15:06.196 --> 15:08.490
just as long as it's not here
at this very moment.

15:11.285 --> 15:12.745
[exhales]

15:12.828 --> 15:14.163
All right.

15:22.963 --> 15:24.006
[chuckles]

15:24.173 --> 15:25.257
-[grunts]
-Ow!

15:25.341 --> 15:26.383
[groaning]

15:27.259 --> 15:29.219
God, you bust my finger.

15:29.553 --> 15:32.139
I wiped that grin
off your shit-poked face, didn't I?

15:32.222 --> 15:34.475
God damn it, Percy,
get the hell off my block!

15:34.808 --> 15:36.310
[Del groaning]

15:39.688 --> 15:40.689
Uh-huh.

15:46.987 --> 15:48.614
[swears in French] Fuck you, Percy.

15:48.697 --> 15:51.951
We're gonna get that looked at, Del.
In the meantime, you just stay quiet.

15:52.785 --> 15:54.495
Yeah. Yeah.

15:58.832 --> 16:01.460
I let Harry take those chains off you,

16:02.044 --> 16:03.170
you gonna be nice?

16:08.717 --> 16:10.219
[keys jangling]

16:20.437 --> 16:21.855
Your name is John Coffey.

16:22.398 --> 16:24.149
Yes, sir, boss.

16:24.233 --> 16:27.194
Like the drink, only not spelt the same.

16:27.945 --> 16:29.363
Oh, you can spell, can you?

16:30.239 --> 16:31.991
Just my name, boss.

16:33.867 --> 16:35.911
J-O...

16:36.537 --> 16:38.539
My name is Paul Edgecomb.

16:39.665 --> 16:42.251
If I'm not here,
you can ask for Mr. Terwilliger,

16:42.334 --> 16:45.462
Mr. Howell or Mr. Stanton,
these gentlemen right there.

16:48.048 --> 16:49.174
Questions?

16:49.925 --> 16:52.261
Do you leave the light on after bedtime?

16:55.014 --> 16:58.225
'Cause I get a little scared
in the dark sometime,

16:59.143 --> 17:01.103
if it's a strange place.

17:06.650 --> 17:09.862
It stays pretty bright
around here all night long.

17:10.904 --> 17:13.407
We always keep a few lights burning
out in the corridor.

17:14.616 --> 17:16.160
The corridor?

17:18.162 --> 17:19.455
Right out there.

17:47.816 --> 17:49.234
You can sit.

17:58.660 --> 18:00.162
[door locking]

18:11.590 --> 18:13.592
I couldn't help it, boss.

18:14.301 --> 18:17.304
I tried to take it back,
but it was too late.

18:22.684 --> 18:24.853
Dean, pull Delacroix's card,

18:24.937 --> 18:27.439
take him down to the infirmary,
see if those fingers are broken.

18:27.523 --> 18:28.774
-Yes, sir.
-Of course they're broken.

18:28.857 --> 18:30.609
I heard the bones crack.

18:30.692 --> 18:33.654
Did you hear what he was yelling
when we brought the big dummy in?

18:33.737 --> 18:35.697
How could I miss it, Harry?
The whole prison heard.

18:36.657 --> 18:37.866
Goddamn Percy.

18:38.826 --> 18:41.453
You'll probably have to answer
for sending him off the Mile.

18:41.537 --> 18:44.289
Hmm. I'll chew that food when I have to.

18:45.165 --> 18:46.458
Right now I wanna hear
about this new inmate.

18:46.542 --> 18:48.085
Aside from how big he is, okay?

18:50.212 --> 18:52.089
Monstrous big. [chuckling] Damn.

18:52.464 --> 18:54.758
Oh, he seems meek enough.

18:54.842 --> 18:56.426
-Is he retarded, you figure?
-Mmm-hmm.

18:57.386 --> 18:59.555
Looks like they sent us
an imbecile to execute.

18:59.638 --> 19:03.016
Imbecile or not,
he deserves to fry for what he done.

19:06.645 --> 19:08.564
Make your blood curdle.

19:21.160 --> 19:22.786
[Marjorie screaming]

19:32.546 --> 19:34.173
What? For God's sake, what?

19:34.256 --> 19:37.176
The girls! The girls are gone!

19:37.509 --> 19:40.012
Papa! Papa, look! There's blood.

19:40.095 --> 19:41.638
[Klaus panting]

19:44.683 --> 19:46.059
Oh, my God.

19:51.607 --> 19:55.861
God damn it, woman! Get on that phone now!
You tell them we headed west.

19:55.944 --> 19:58.739
You mind what I'm saying! We headed west!

19:59.364 --> 20:01.575
Central! Are you on the line?

20:01.950 --> 20:05.412
Oh, God, please!
Somebody took my little girls!

20:13.253 --> 20:14.755
[dogs barking]

20:17.466 --> 20:18.967
Katie!

20:20.260 --> 20:21.678
Cora!

20:34.650 --> 20:36.193
[man screaming]

20:47.871 --> 20:49.164
[sobbing]

20:52.918 --> 20:54.086
Jesus.

20:55.337 --> 20:56.505
Jesus.

21:07.766 --> 21:08.850
I'll kill you!

21:08.934 --> 21:10.269
[groaning]

21:12.688 --> 21:14.189
I'll kill you!

21:16.525 --> 21:17.776
[yelling]

21:26.576 --> 21:28.120
[flies buzzing]

21:28.203 --> 21:29.204
[gasping]

21:33.709 --> 21:34.960
[sobbing]

21:42.217 --> 21:44.177
I... I couldn't help it.

21:45.929 --> 21:48.932
I tried to take it back,
but it was too late.

21:53.103 --> 21:55.522
Boy, you under arrest for murder.

21:58.483 --> 21:59.776
[Hal] I interrupt?

22:02.654 --> 22:04.698
Well, I'm just about done.

22:14.041 --> 22:15.083
Hey,

22:16.001 --> 22:17.419
how's that pretty gal of yours?

22:19.379 --> 22:21.506
Melinda's not so well, Paul.

22:22.382 --> 22:23.467
Not so well at all.

22:25.552 --> 22:26.762
More headaches?

22:27.471 --> 22:30.182
Got laid up with another one yesterday.

22:30.599 --> 22:32.100
Worst one yet.

22:32.893 --> 22:37.022
I'll be taking her over to Vicksburg
next day or so for some tests.

22:37.773 --> 22:40.317
Head X-rays and who knows what else.

22:40.734 --> 22:43.028
She is scared to death.

22:45.614 --> 22:47.532
Truth to tell, so am I.

22:48.867 --> 22:51.787
If it's something they can
see on the X-ray,

22:52.412 --> 22:54.081
maybe it's something they can fix.

22:55.207 --> 22:56.374
Maybe.

23:01.004 --> 23:02.839
This just came in.

23:02.923 --> 23:04.591
DOE on Bitterbuck.

23:08.220 --> 23:10.597
You didn't come all the way down here
just to hand me a DOE.

23:11.765 --> 23:15.727
I had an angry call from
the state capitol about 20 minutes ago.

23:16.436 --> 23:18.396
Is it true you ordered
Percy Wetmore off the block?

23:18.480 --> 23:19.481
It is.

23:21.149 --> 23:23.568
Now, I'm sure you had reason, Paul,

23:23.652 --> 23:25.904
but like it or not,

23:25.987 --> 23:28.782
the wife of the governor of this state
has only one nephew,

23:28.865 --> 23:30.909
and his name happens to be Percy Wetmore.

23:30.992 --> 23:36.081
Little Percy calls his aunt
and squeals like a schoolroom sissy.

23:38.125 --> 23:42.504
He also mention he assaulted a prisoner
this morning out of sheer petulance?

23:42.587 --> 23:45.465
Broke three fingers
on Eduard Delacroix's left hand?

23:45.549 --> 23:48.009
I didn't hear that part.
I'm sure she didn't either.

23:48.093 --> 23:50.303
The man is mean and careless and stupid,

23:50.387 --> 23:52.597
and that's a bad combination
in a place like this.

23:53.515 --> 23:55.600
Sooner or later,
he's gonna get somebody hurt or worse.

23:55.684 --> 23:57.727
Stick with it, Paul.

23:57.811 --> 23:59.604
It may not be much longer.

23:59.688 --> 24:01.690
I have it on good authority

24:01.773 --> 24:03.567
that Percy has an application
in at Briar Ridge.

24:04.401 --> 24:07.112
Briar Ridge? The mental hospital.

24:07.195 --> 24:08.405
Administration job.

24:08.822 --> 24:10.448
Better pay.

24:10.532 --> 24:11.783
Hmm.

24:11.867 --> 24:13.910
Then why is he still here?

24:15.620 --> 24:18.206
He can get that application
pushed through.

24:18.665 --> 24:19.708
Hmm.

24:20.458 --> 24:23.545
Hell, with his connections,
he could have any state job he wants.

24:24.379 --> 24:26.214
You know what I think?

24:28.216 --> 24:31.303
I think he just wants to
see one cook up close.

24:34.681 --> 24:37.809
Well, he'll get his chance, then,
won't he?

24:39.519 --> 24:41.980
Maybe then he'll be satisfied and move on.

24:42.063 --> 24:43.648
In the meantime,

24:44.149 --> 24:46.568
-you'll keep the peace?
-Of course.

24:48.486 --> 24:49.696
Of course.

24:50.739 --> 24:52.741
[patting] Thank you, Paul.

24:56.286 --> 24:57.370
Hal,

24:59.080 --> 25:01.708
you give Melinda my love, okay?

25:01.791 --> 25:05.253
I'm sure that X-ray
will turn out to be nothing at all.

25:07.464 --> 25:08.715
You bet.

25:16.431 --> 25:18.767
[soft music playing on radio]

25:35.408 --> 25:36.409
[Jan] Paul.

25:37.410 --> 25:38.787
-Hey, you.
-Hey.

25:39.746 --> 25:41.081
The music too loud?

25:43.124 --> 25:45.085
There's just this
big, empty spot in the bed

25:45.168 --> 25:46.753
where my husband usually sleeps.

25:49.464 --> 25:53.551
He said to tell you he's having a little
trouble with that tonight. [sighs]

25:56.638 --> 25:58.890
Worried about Melinda and Hal?

25:59.516 --> 26:01.559
Is that what's got you up?

26:01.977 --> 26:03.478
Yeah, that

26:05.563 --> 26:07.065
and things.

26:07.941 --> 26:09.150
Things.

26:13.822 --> 26:16.157
We got a new inmate today.

26:17.534 --> 26:19.327
Simple-minded fella.

26:20.954 --> 26:23.081
Do I wanna know what he did?

26:24.207 --> 26:25.500
-No.
-Mmm.

26:26.751 --> 26:29.170
Things that happen in this world...

26:30.422 --> 26:32.549
It's a wonder God allows it.

26:37.053 --> 26:39.097
Why don't you come to bed?

26:39.723 --> 26:42.434
I think I have something
to help you sleep.

26:42.517 --> 26:43.518
[Paul] Mmm.

26:43.601 --> 26:45.895
Mmm. You can have all you want.

26:47.522 --> 26:50.150
I still got something wrong
with my waterworks.

26:50.233 --> 26:52.444
I don't wanna pass it on to you.

26:52.527 --> 26:54.946
-Have you seen Doc Bishop yet?
-No.

26:55.030 --> 26:56.197
[sighs] Paul.

26:57.073 --> 26:58.074
[sighs]

26:58.158 --> 27:00.368
Because he's just gonna want me
to take sulfa tablets,

27:00.452 --> 27:02.996
and I'll spend the rest of the week
puking in every corner in my office.

27:03.079 --> 27:07.042
It will run its course all by itself.
Thank you very much for your concern.

27:10.128 --> 27:11.588
Poor old guy.

27:13.923 --> 27:14.966
Oh.

27:21.056 --> 27:22.724
[Brutal laughing]

27:26.061 --> 27:27.812
[Brutal] Paul. Dean.

27:32.567 --> 27:33.610
Yeah?

27:34.319 --> 27:36.029
[mouthing] Come here. Go on.

27:39.115 --> 27:41.576
I guess the legislature
loosened up the purse strings enough

27:41.659 --> 27:43.578
to hire on a new guard.

27:52.504 --> 27:54.005
Look again.

27:54.089 --> 27:55.340
He's right

27:55.757 --> 27:57.050
there.

28:06.017 --> 28:08.853
It ain't normal for a mouse
to come up on people this way.

28:09.604 --> 28:10.688
Maybe it's rabid.

28:10.772 --> 28:12.065
-Oh, yeah, yeah.
-Oh, my Christ.

28:12.148 --> 28:14.984
-Yeah, it could be.
-Oh, the big mouse expert.

28:15.693 --> 28:18.071
-The mouse man.
-[sighs]

28:18.154 --> 28:20.490
What, you see him foaming
at the mouth, Mouse Man?

28:20.698 --> 28:21.950
I don't see its mouth at all.

28:22.033 --> 28:23.451
[sniggering]

28:31.709 --> 28:33.211
Oh, Brutal, no.

28:33.294 --> 28:36.297
-We'll be hip-deep in mice around here.
-I just wanna see what he'll do.

28:36.798 --> 28:38.883
In the interest of science, like.

29:05.910 --> 29:06.911
[squeaks]

29:19.507 --> 29:21.634
He's in the damn restraint room.

29:21.718 --> 29:23.636
And you just know
he's chewing the padding out of the walls,

29:23.720 --> 29:26.181
making himself a nice little nest.

29:29.017 --> 29:30.226
[clicks tongue]

29:31.603 --> 29:32.937
All right.

29:33.688 --> 29:35.857
Let's go get the damn mouse.

29:47.619 --> 29:48.620
[Coffey] Boss.

29:49.329 --> 29:51.122
Saw me a mouse go by.

29:51.748 --> 29:53.541
Can't put anything over on you.

30:03.384 --> 30:05.720
[murmuring indistinctly]

30:05.804 --> 30:07.806
[Paul] All right. Just watch your toes.
Watch your toes.

30:07.889 --> 30:09.557
-Yeah. All right.
-Here we go.

30:26.908 --> 30:28.201
You let him get past you.

30:28.910 --> 30:31.412
No, I did not.
I've been here all the time.

30:31.496 --> 30:33.498
Then where the hell is he?

30:33.581 --> 30:35.333
Well, I don't know.

30:36.251 --> 30:37.418
[sighs]

30:37.502 --> 30:39.045
Three grown men

30:40.213 --> 30:42.090
outsmarted by a mouse.

30:44.717 --> 30:46.344
[exhales] Well,

30:46.427 --> 30:50.056
bright side is, all this commotion
probably scared him off for good.

30:50.139 --> 30:52.016
[chuckles] Yeah, yeah.

30:52.851 --> 30:55.562
Yeah, that's the last we'll see of him.

30:56.771 --> 30:58.439
[Percy whistling]

31:29.304 --> 31:30.889
[soft squeaking]

31:38.938 --> 31:40.565
[stops whistling]

31:46.821 --> 31:48.823
You little son of a bitch.

31:51.367 --> 31:53.578
[Harry] Well, I'll be damned.

31:53.661 --> 31:58.166
There he is, big as Billy-be-frigged.
I thought Brutal was pulling my leg.

31:59.334 --> 32:01.169
-And that's a goddamn mouse.
-Yeah.

32:02.211 --> 32:04.839
Brute said he was in here last night,

32:05.590 --> 32:07.216
begging for food.

32:07.634 --> 32:09.677
He comes right on up to the desk.

32:11.012 --> 32:12.597
-Give him some room, Percy.
-Huh?

32:12.680 --> 32:15.099
-Yeah, see what he does.
-All right.

32:26.486 --> 32:29.656
[whispers] He's a brave little bastard.
Gotta give him that.

32:55.181 --> 32:56.182
[yells]

32:57.850 --> 32:59.978
-[metal clanking]
-[Percy] Damn!

33:00.311 --> 33:02.730
[screams] You little scurvy! Damn!

33:03.690 --> 33:06.734
Percy, are you crazy,
you little son of a bitch?

33:07.235 --> 33:09.070
-I'm gonna kill you!
-Percy!

33:09.487 --> 33:10.530
[grunts]

33:10.613 --> 33:13.408
-I'm gonna take you out!
-Percy! Percy!

33:13.491 --> 33:17.537
You little vermin!
I'm gonna stomp your life out!

33:17.620 --> 33:19.372
It's just a little mouse, dumb <i>merde.</i>

33:19.455 --> 33:21.749
You ugly little piece of...

33:23.084 --> 33:24.627
-[Harry] Are you listening to me?
-Fuck!

33:24.919 --> 33:28.256
-Percy!
-I'm gonna rip your diseased head off,

33:28.756 --> 33:30.091
you little piece of shit!

33:31.134 --> 33:34.262
[Percy] Get on out of there!
[Harry] I want you to stop this!

33:35.096 --> 33:37.598
Pipe down. I'm talking to you.

33:41.602 --> 33:43.104
Percy.

33:43.187 --> 33:45.189
-[prisoner 1] Hey, boss!
-Hey, Captain, What's going on?

33:51.279 --> 33:53.114
Percy met your mouse.

33:55.742 --> 33:57.535
It's in here somewhere.

33:57.618 --> 33:59.871
I'm gonna squish
the little son of a bitch.

34:02.623 --> 34:05.168
Percy, we already tried that.

34:07.336 --> 34:08.337
Huh?

34:08.713 --> 34:10.214
What'd you say?

34:10.298 --> 34:11.966
I said that we...

34:16.095 --> 34:18.765
Knock yourself out.
Hope you nail the bastard.

34:20.183 --> 34:21.809
[pants] Oh, yeah.

34:24.896 --> 34:26.481
[panting]

34:33.654 --> 34:35.865
Gosh. He ain't in there, huh?

34:36.449 --> 34:38.743
Don't that beat the mousy band?

34:42.038 --> 34:43.206
Percy,

34:45.208 --> 34:47.502
you wanna think about
what you were doing just now?

34:47.794 --> 34:51.005
I was trying to get the mouse.
Are you blind?

34:51.589 --> 34:54.842
You also scared the living crap
out of me and Bill,

34:55.301 --> 34:56.886
not to mention the inmates.

34:57.220 --> 34:58.596
So what?

34:58.679 --> 35:02.183
They aren't in cradle school,
in case you didn't notice.

35:02.850 --> 35:05.061
Although you treat 'em that way
half the time.

35:05.144 --> 35:08.356
We don't scare them
any more than we have to, Percy.

35:08.439 --> 35:12.318
-They're under enough strain as it is.
-Men under strain can snap.

35:13.027 --> 35:15.947
Hurt themselves and hurt others.
That's why our job is

35:17.073 --> 35:18.449
talking,

35:19.200 --> 35:20.576
not yelling.

35:21.536 --> 35:23.037
You'd do better to think of this place

35:23.121 --> 35:24.831
like it's an intensive care ward
of a hospital.

35:25.373 --> 35:28.459
I think of it as a bucket of piss
to drown rats in.

35:29.168 --> 35:30.545
That's all.

35:31.420 --> 35:33.631
Anybody doesn't like it? Hmm?

35:33.714 --> 35:35.466
You can kiss my ass.

35:36.801 --> 35:38.970
[grunts] Don't. Yeah, you try it. Go on.

35:39.053 --> 35:40.304
Try it.

35:40.388 --> 35:42.807
You'll be on the bread lines
before the week is out.

35:43.224 --> 35:44.725
Okay, Brutal. [patting]

35:57.238 --> 35:59.448
We all know
who your connections are, Percy.

36:00.074 --> 36:02.493
You ever threaten a man
on this block again,

36:02.577 --> 36:03.744
we all gonna have a go.

36:04.495 --> 36:05.830
Job be damned.

36:08.457 --> 36:09.750
You done?

36:13.087 --> 36:15.173
Get all this shit back
in the restraining room.

36:15.256 --> 36:17.216
You are cluttering up my Mile.

36:34.108 --> 36:36.819
-[footsteps approaching]
-[keys jangling]

36:39.447 --> 36:40.615
Arlen,

36:41.032 --> 36:43.326
your daughter and her family are here.

36:49.749 --> 36:53.085
Let's move. I want at least
two rehearsals before he gets back.

36:53.169 --> 36:54.462
[door opening]

36:57.006 --> 36:58.966
Uh, settle down, settle down!

36:59.050 --> 37:01.219
Rehearsing now. Everybody settle!

37:01.302 --> 37:03.262
Arlen Bitterbuck, step forward.

37:03.888 --> 37:07.308
Stepping forward, stepping forward,
stepping forward.

37:07.391 --> 37:10.853
-Is his head properly shaved?
-Nope. It's all dandruffy, and it smells.

37:10.937 --> 37:13.814
I will take that as a yes.
Let's go, Arlen.

37:14.857 --> 37:17.360
Walking the Mile, walking the Mile,

37:17.985 --> 37:21.155
walking the Mile, walking the Mile,

37:21.239 --> 37:22.240
walking the Mile,

37:22.323 --> 37:24.075
walking the Mile.

37:24.158 --> 37:27.245
I'm getting to my knees.
I'm praying, praying.

37:27.328 --> 37:30.039
Lord is my shepherd
and so forth and so on.

37:30.289 --> 37:34.669
I'm sorry for all the bad shit I've done
and people I've tramped on and everything.

37:35.044 --> 37:36.170
And I hope they forgive me,

37:36.254 --> 37:39.173
and I'll never do it again,

37:39.257 --> 37:40.299
that's for sure.

37:40.549 --> 37:44.387
Paul, we're not gonna have some
Cherokee medicine man in here,

37:44.470 --> 37:46.555
hooping, hollering
and shaking his dick, are we?

37:46.639 --> 37:49.058
-Well, actually--
-[Toot-Toot] Still praying, still praying.

37:49.141 --> 37:50.768
Getting right with Jesus.

37:50.851 --> 37:53.020
Do it quietly, you old gink!

37:53.980 --> 37:56.774
As I was saying, I don't believe
they actually shake their dicks, Harry.

37:57.775 --> 37:59.902
Be that as it may,
Mr. Bitterbuck is a Christian,

37:59.986 --> 38:01.362
so we've got Reverend Schuster coming in.

38:01.445 --> 38:05.157
Oh, he's good. He's fast, too.
Doesn't get 'em all worked up.

38:05.241 --> 38:08.286
On your feet. Come on, Toot.
You prayed enough for one day.

38:08.369 --> 38:10.621
Getting to my feet. Walking the Mile,

38:10.705 --> 38:12.623
walking the Mile, walking the Mile,

38:12.707 --> 38:14.625
walking the Green Mile.

38:14.917 --> 38:16.460
Walking the Mile.

38:16.544 --> 38:18.337
Walking in the Mile.

38:19.380 --> 38:21.048
Sitting down now.

38:22.049 --> 38:23.050
Sitting down.

38:23.676 --> 38:25.594
I'm taking a seat in Old Sparky.

38:26.053 --> 38:27.054
What do I do?

38:28.097 --> 38:31.100
-Watch and learn.
-[Toot-Toot] Watch and learn.

38:36.564 --> 38:38.107
Getting strapped.

38:39.233 --> 38:40.860
Getting clamped.

38:42.570 --> 38:44.071
Gettin' wired.

38:46.073 --> 38:47.408
All right.

38:48.451 --> 38:50.328
Getting all electrode.

38:56.417 --> 38:57.460
[Brutal] Roll on one.

38:58.502 --> 39:01.672
"Roll on one" means
I turn the generator up full.

39:01.756 --> 39:04.008
You see the lights go brighter
in half the prison.

39:04.091 --> 39:05.926
[Brutal] Arlen Bitterbuck,

39:06.010 --> 39:08.888
you've been condemned to die
by a jury of your peers,

39:08.971 --> 39:12.058
sentence imposed by a judge
in good standing in this state.

39:12.600 --> 39:14.935
You have anything to say
before your sentence is carried out?

39:15.436 --> 39:16.520
Yeah.

39:16.937 --> 39:20.149
I want a fried chicken dinner
with gravy on the taters,

39:20.232 --> 39:21.650
and I want to shit in your hat.

39:22.276 --> 39:26.572
I got to have Mae West sit on my face
'cause I'm one horny motherfucker.

39:26.655 --> 39:27.990
[laughing]

39:31.869 --> 39:32.995
You bastard.

39:33.871 --> 39:35.998
[Toot-Toot] That's a good one.

39:36.082 --> 39:37.249
[Paul] Quiet.

39:37.666 --> 39:38.709
Quiet! Shut up!

39:38.793 --> 39:40.669
-Shut up!
-Sorry, boss.

39:41.670 --> 39:45.091
Toot, one more remark like that,
I'll have Van Hay roll on two for real.

39:46.133 --> 39:48.511
And I'll have one less crazy old trusty
in the world.

39:49.387 --> 39:50.721
It was pretty funny.

39:50.805 --> 39:51.847
That's why I don't like it.

39:51.931 --> 39:53.474
We'll be doing this
for real tomorrow night.

39:54.141 --> 39:56.352
I don't want anybody remembering
some stupid joke like that

39:56.435 --> 39:57.478
and getting going again.

39:58.729 --> 39:59.814
You ever try not to laugh in church

39:59.897 --> 40:01.065
when something funny
gets stuck in your head?

40:01.148 --> 40:03.275
It's the same goddamn thing.

40:04.151 --> 40:06.404
I'm sorry, Paul. You're right.

40:06.487 --> 40:07.988
Let's keep going.

40:08.072 --> 40:09.240
Harry.

40:13.744 --> 40:15.329
Soak the sponge.

40:18.290 --> 40:20.876
[Toot-Toot] Putting on the black hood.

40:23.838 --> 40:25.423
And I'm putting on my cap.

40:25.506 --> 40:27.466
Why's he putting that sponge on his head?

40:27.550 --> 40:30.594
Conducts electricity
directly to the brain, fast like a bullet.

40:31.762 --> 40:34.056
You don't ever throw the switch
on a man without that.

40:34.140 --> 40:35.891
[Toot-Toot mimics gurgling]

40:37.726 --> 40:39.061
[Paul] Hush up there, Toot.

40:39.145 --> 40:40.146
[grunts]

40:42.523 --> 40:44.650
[Toot-Toot] Getting screwed.

40:45.067 --> 40:46.861
I'm getting the cap.

40:49.321 --> 40:50.531
[sighs]

40:51.574 --> 40:53.075
[Brutal] Arlen Bitterbuck,

40:53.159 --> 40:56.662
the electricity shall now be passed
through your body until you are dead

40:56.745 --> 40:58.956
in accordance with state law.

40:59.707 --> 41:01.834
God have mercy on your soul.

41:03.335 --> 41:04.420
Amen.

41:07.047 --> 41:08.090
Roll on two.

41:11.969 --> 41:12.970
And that's that.

41:13.929 --> 41:15.681
[Toot-Toot yelling]

41:16.724 --> 41:19.477
I'm frying! I'm frying!

41:21.812 --> 41:23.939
I'm a done tom turkey!

41:24.023 --> 41:25.357
[chuckles]

41:26.567 --> 41:28.277
This is a shocking experience!

41:30.237 --> 41:33.157
One of the witnesses showed up
a day early.

41:37.328 --> 41:39.079
[Toot-Toot] Goodbye.

41:40.372 --> 41:42.958
All right. Let's do it again,
and let's get it right this time.

41:43.417 --> 41:45.753
Get that idiot out of the chair.

42:45.604 --> 42:49.441
Do you think if a man sincerely repents
on what he done wrong,

42:51.402 --> 42:54.905
that he might get to go back to the time
that was happiest for him,

42:54.989 --> 42:56.865
and live there forever?

42:59.827 --> 43:01.579
Could that be what heaven's like?

43:03.038 --> 43:05.666
I just about believe that very thing.

43:08.794 --> 43:09.837
Hmm.

43:11.839 --> 43:14.300
Had me a young wife when I was 18.

43:15.676 --> 43:19.555
Spent our first summer in the mountains.
Made love every night.

43:21.015 --> 43:23.350
And she'd lie there after,

43:25.102 --> 43:27.396
bare-breasted in the firelight.

43:28.772 --> 43:31.775
And we'd talk sometimes
till the sun come up.

43:35.154 --> 43:37.031
That was my best time.

43:50.919 --> 43:52.504
[inhales deeply]

43:52.588 --> 43:53.881
[exhales]

43:57.593 --> 43:59.386
[Paul] It'll be fine.

44:00.429 --> 44:01.972
You'll do fine.

44:16.070 --> 44:18.072
[Arlen breathing heavily]

44:38.175 --> 44:39.718
[Brutal] Arlen Bitterbuck,

44:39.802 --> 44:42.262
electricity shall now be passed
through your body

44:42.346 --> 44:45.516
until you are dead,
in accordance with state law.

44:46.433 --> 44:48.602
-God have mercy on your soul.
-[breathing rapidly]

45:08.497 --> 45:09.706
Roll on two.

45:10.666 --> 45:13.460
-[electricity sizzling]
-[grunting]

45:32.688 --> 45:33.730
[electricity stops]

45:54.334 --> 45:55.377
Again.

45:56.211 --> 45:58.714
[electricity sizzling]

46:02.301 --> 46:04.261
[Percy] <i>Adios,</i> Chief.

46:04.344 --> 46:08.307
Drop us a card from hell.
Let us know if it's hot enough.

46:11.602 --> 46:13.520
He's paid what he owed.

46:14.146 --> 46:16.440
He's square with the house again.

46:16.523 --> 46:19.026
So keep your goddamn hands off him.

46:39.296 --> 46:41.340
What's up his ass?

46:41.423 --> 46:42.758
You.

46:43.675 --> 46:45.969
Always. You, Percy.

46:46.845 --> 46:50.057
Oh, you gotta hate the new boy?
That the way it is around here?

46:52.017 --> 46:55.229
Why don't you just move on?
Take that job at Briar Ridge?

46:55.938 --> 46:58.440
Hmm? Oh, yeah. I know all about it.

46:59.233 --> 47:02.402
Sounds to me like a pretty good job.

47:04.071 --> 47:07.282
Yeah, I might just take it, too,
soon as you put me out front.

47:08.617 --> 47:09.952
Yeah, you heard me.

47:10.536 --> 47:13.121
I want Brutal's spot
for the next execution.

47:16.750 --> 47:18.835
Seeing a man die, now that's not enough.

47:18.919 --> 47:21.171
You gotta be close enough
to smell his nuts cook.

47:21.255 --> 47:23.257
I just wanna be out front, is all.

47:24.883 --> 47:26.885
Come on. One time.

47:28.095 --> 47:29.680
And then you know what?

47:29.763 --> 47:32.516
You'll be rid of me. I swear.

47:33.058 --> 47:34.309
And if l say no?

47:36.061 --> 47:39.356
Well, l might just stick around for good.

47:40.232 --> 47:41.984
Make me a career of this.

47:43.443 --> 47:44.778
Boss.

47:46.655 --> 47:47.864
[sighs]

47:58.792 --> 48:01.920
[soft music playing on radio]

48:06.133 --> 48:08.135
[shuddering]

48:17.227 --> 48:19.646
[Del laughing]

48:32.284 --> 48:33.744
[music stops]

48:37.664 --> 48:38.999
You are not gonna believe this.

48:49.426 --> 48:50.761
Look.

48:52.387 --> 48:54.431
I done tame me that mouse.

48:55.891 --> 48:57.267
We see that.

48:57.351 --> 49:01.521
Oh, oh. Watch this. Watch what he do.

49:04.358 --> 49:05.942
[continues laughing]

49:09.404 --> 49:10.405
Ain't he something now?

49:12.240 --> 49:14.534
He's smart, Mr. Jingles.

49:14.618 --> 49:16.745
-Mr. Jingles?
-That his name.

49:17.329 --> 49:19.206
He whispered in my ear.

49:20.040 --> 49:21.208
Hey, Captain.

49:21.291 --> 49:24.878
Could I have a box for my mouse
so he can sleep in here with me?

49:24.961 --> 49:27.631
I notice your English gets better
when you want something.

49:28.006 --> 49:29.883
Wanna see what else he can do?

49:30.634 --> 49:32.636
Hmm? Watch, watch, watch.

49:33.136 --> 49:36.181
Mr. Jingle? Mr. Jingle, wanna play fetch?

49:36.431 --> 49:38.392
Wanna play fetch? [speaking French]

49:38.934 --> 49:40.936
Play fetch. Watch, watch, watch.

49:48.777 --> 49:50.654
[Del chuckling]

50:00.789 --> 50:03.125
He fetch it every time. Every time.

50:03.917 --> 50:08.338
That's some smart mouse, Del.
Like he a circus mouse or somethin'.

50:10.924 --> 50:14.094
Correct. That just what he is, too.
He's a circus mouse.

50:14.302 --> 50:16.138
When I get out of here,
he's gonna make me rich.

50:16.722 --> 50:19.141
You just watch and see
if he don't do that.

50:19.224 --> 50:21.393
Play fetch? We play fetch again?

50:22.269 --> 50:24.187
[Percy] Well, well, well.

50:24.271 --> 50:26.398
Looks like you found yourself
a new friend there, Del.

50:27.190 --> 50:28.525
Don't hurt him.

50:30.110 --> 50:32.446
-Okay?
-Is that the one l chased?

50:33.071 --> 50:35.157
Yeah, that's the one.

50:35.240 --> 50:38.201
Only Del says his name is Mr. Jingles.

50:39.453 --> 50:40.454
Is that so?

50:41.872 --> 50:43.540
Del's been asking for a box.

50:44.291 --> 50:46.084
Thinks the mouse will sleep in it,
I guess.

50:46.376 --> 50:48.003
Might keep it for a pet.

50:50.630 --> 50:51.798
What do you think?

50:52.966 --> 50:56.595
You know what?
We ought to find a cigar box,

50:57.429 --> 51:01.433
and, uh, get some cotton batting
from the dispensary to line it with.

51:02.559 --> 51:04.186
Yeah.

51:04.269 --> 51:06.396
Yeah. That should do real nice.

51:16.698 --> 51:18.700
Man said get a cigar box.

51:21.411 --> 51:23.622
[telephone ringing distantly]

51:28.752 --> 51:30.170
[secretary] Morning.

51:35.008 --> 51:36.468
Hal, you wanted to see me?

51:37.344 --> 51:38.428
Yeah.

51:39.221 --> 51:40.764
Close the door.

51:46.520 --> 51:48.063
[clears throat]

51:48.146 --> 51:49.439
So you know...

51:49.523 --> 51:51.191
[sniffles]

51:51.274 --> 51:53.693
You got a new prisoner
coming in here tomorrow.

51:54.820 --> 51:56.404
William Wharton.

51:57.364 --> 51:58.698
He's what you call

51:59.533 --> 52:00.534
a problem child.

52:02.160 --> 52:05.038
Got "Billy the Kid" tattooed
on his left arm.

52:06.081 --> 52:09.709
Been rambling all over the state
last few years,

52:10.544 --> 52:12.712
causing all kinds of trouble.

52:13.421 --> 52:15.423
Finally hit the big time.

52:16.883 --> 52:19.636
Killed three people in a holdup.

52:20.387 --> 52:22.597
One of them a pregnant woman.

52:24.850 --> 52:26.601
Bad news all around.

52:28.603 --> 52:29.688
Hal?

52:41.366 --> 52:42.576
It's a tumor, Paul.

52:44.286 --> 52:45.787
A brain tumor.

52:47.747 --> 52:49.624
They got

52:49.708 --> 52:51.293
X-ray pictures of it.

52:53.295 --> 52:55.338
It's the size of a lemon, they said.

52:58.508 --> 52:59.676
And

53:00.927 --> 53:02.262
way down

53:04.306 --> 53:06.433
deep inside, where they can't operate.

53:08.518 --> 53:10.270
I haven't told her.

53:11.938 --> 53:13.607
I can't think how.

53:17.777 --> 53:19.863
For the life of me, Paul,

53:21.406 --> 53:23.825
I can't think how to tell my wife

53:27.871 --> 53:29.623
she's going to die.

53:30.457 --> 53:31.708
[sobbing]

53:53.730 --> 53:55.023
[groaning softly]

53:59.277 --> 54:00.487
[grunts]

54:05.659 --> 54:07.285
[panting]

54:15.502 --> 54:17.128
[dogs barking distantly]

54:18.213 --> 54:19.547
[grunting]

54:28.348 --> 54:29.349
Oh.

54:29.891 --> 54:30.934
Ah.

54:35.230 --> 54:36.314
Aah.

54:37.857 --> 54:39.109
[groans]

54:41.194 --> 54:42.487
[exhales]

54:48.785 --> 54:50.036
[coughs]

54:54.290 --> 54:56.126
Oh... Oh, God.

54:57.168 --> 54:58.712
Oh, God.

55:02.799 --> 55:04.217
I'm going.

55:04.300 --> 55:07.554
-What?
-To see Dr. Bishop. I'm going.

55:08.722 --> 55:10.223
Today.

55:10.682 --> 55:12.892
Soon as we get that new inmate
squared away.

55:13.560 --> 55:14.853
That bad?

55:15.520 --> 55:16.771
Oh, yeah.

55:20.191 --> 55:22.068
[man sobbing distantly]

55:25.030 --> 55:26.614
[door unlocking]

55:39.169 --> 55:41.296
The boy is doped to the gills.

55:42.714 --> 55:43.923
Hmm?

55:44.257 --> 55:45.425
Dean, hand me them clothes.

55:48.553 --> 55:50.138
William Wharton?

55:50.930 --> 55:53.850
Hey! You put on these clothes now,
you hear?

55:54.601 --> 55:56.269
[mumbling]

56:02.233 --> 56:03.359
We're gonna have to do this.

56:05.445 --> 56:07.113
[Percy] Hellraiser, huh?

56:07.363 --> 56:09.365
Look more like a limp noodle to me.

56:09.991 --> 56:11.284
Hey.

56:11.951 --> 56:13.244
Hey.

56:13.828 --> 56:15.080
You've been declared competent, son.

56:16.414 --> 56:17.540
You know what that means?

56:18.333 --> 56:20.794
It means you're gonna ride the lightning.
Yeah.

56:20.877 --> 56:22.462
[chuckling]

56:22.545 --> 56:24.547
Percy, could you shut up,
give us a hand here?

56:25.507 --> 56:26.883
Hellraiser.

56:32.180 --> 56:33.890
[indistinct conversations]

56:48.988 --> 56:50.615
[toilet flushing]

56:58.164 --> 56:59.666
[Del] Boss, you don't look so good.

57:01.793 --> 57:03.753
Look like you're running you a fever.

57:03.837 --> 57:05.672
[phone ringing]

57:09.551 --> 57:11.427
[Coffey] Boss Edgecomb?

57:12.637 --> 57:14.556
I needs to see you down here, boss.

57:17.142 --> 57:19.394
I got things to tend to just now,
John Coffey. You just...

57:22.105 --> 57:24.858
You just stay still in your cell.

57:25.900 --> 57:28.236
[phone continues ringing]

57:37.078 --> 57:38.329
E Block.

57:47.630 --> 57:49.674
[indistinct conversations]

58:14.407 --> 58:16.075
[Dean] Come on, let's go.

58:17.118 --> 58:19.329
Come on. Look alive, big boy.

58:33.968 --> 58:35.261
[softly] Careful.

58:38.806 --> 58:41.851
-Careful.
-[Dean] Step up. Step up.

58:43.853 --> 58:45.355
[gate opening]

58:49.776 --> 58:50.777
[grunts]

58:50.985 --> 58:52.612
[yelling]

58:54.822 --> 58:56.157
[whooping]

59:00.954 --> 59:01.955
[grunting]

59:04.874 --> 59:06.125
[grunts]

59:09.879 --> 59:11.548
[laughing]

59:16.427 --> 59:17.637
Where you going? Where you going?

59:20.932 --> 59:22.225
[Wharton yelling]

59:22.725 --> 59:23.977
Ain't this a party now?

59:24.352 --> 59:25.562
-Is it or what?
-Let him go.

59:25.853 --> 59:27.313
-[Dean] Shoot him.
-Shoot! See who you hit.

59:27.689 --> 59:29.315
-[Dean] Shoot the son of a bitch.
-Come on, shoot me!

59:29.691 --> 59:32.860
-Shoot him!
-Hit him, Percy! God damn it! Hit him.

59:33.361 --> 59:34.779
Hit me, you limp noodle.

59:34.862 --> 59:37.156
Hit him, Percy! God damn it, hit him!

59:37.532 --> 59:40.368
-Come on, Percy. Hit me.
-Wharton, I'm warning you.

59:40.702 --> 59:43.288
-You warning me? Warn me now.
-[Paul] I'm warning you!

59:43.371 --> 59:45.331
-You're warning me?
-[Dean] Shoot him!

59:45.999 --> 59:47.166
-Well, come on...
-[grunts]

59:48.835 --> 59:50.086
[panting]

59:50.169 --> 59:51.421
[clicks safety on]

59:51.504 --> 59:52.839
[groans]

59:53.673 --> 59:54.841
You're a big fucker.

59:56.092 --> 59:57.260
Where'd you come from?

59:57.343 --> 59:58.553
[grunts]

59:59.679 --> 1:00:00.847
[Dean grunting]

1:00:08.062 --> 1:00:10.315
[Brutal] Come on, Dean.
Come on, boy, get up.

1:00:10.398 --> 1:00:12.191
-[gasping]
-All right. Now, just breathe.

1:00:12.817 --> 1:00:14.944
That's it. Just breathe. Just breathe.

1:00:16.863 --> 1:00:18.823
Breathe. Breathe, boy.

1:00:18.906 --> 1:00:20.325
-[Dean] Didn't see it coming.
-Come on, boy, breathe.

1:00:20.408 --> 1:00:21.993
[Dean] Didn't see it coming.

1:00:22.076 --> 1:00:23.953
Come on. Just breathe.

1:00:26.789 --> 1:00:28.750
We thought he was doped.

1:00:30.209 --> 1:00:33.588
Didn't we?
Didn't we all of us think he was doped?

1:00:33.671 --> 1:00:35.340
You didn't ask?

1:00:36.716 --> 1:00:38.509
Well, l guess that's not a mistake

1:00:39.052 --> 1:00:41.888
you'll be needing to make again
anytime soon, is it?

1:00:56.235 --> 1:00:59.447
You go get Dean and Harry looked at.
Make sure they're all right.

1:01:00.406 --> 1:01:03.284
Percy, you make the report
to the warden for me.

1:01:04.077 --> 1:01:05.662
Start out by saying
the situation's under control.

1:01:05.745 --> 1:01:06.788
It's not a story.

1:01:06.871 --> 1:01:09.624
He will not appreciate you
drawing out the suspense.

1:01:09.707 --> 1:01:12.126
Well, what about you?
You're about ready to collapse.

1:01:12.210 --> 1:01:15.213
Ah, I've got the Mile
till you all come back.

1:01:16.297 --> 1:01:17.840
Go on, now. Go.

1:01:23.554 --> 1:01:24.764
[grunts softly]

1:01:25.932 --> 1:01:28.935
[Brutal] Come on, boy.
Let's get you looked at.

1:01:33.606 --> 1:01:34.774
-[door closes]
-[breathing heavily]

1:01:54.711 --> 1:01:57.630
[Coffey] Boss,
I needs to see you down here.

1:02:01.676 --> 1:02:05.054
This is not a good time, John Coffey.

1:02:05.138 --> 1:02:07.140
Not a good time at all.

1:02:07.223 --> 1:02:11.227
But l needs to see you, boss.
I needs to talk to you.

1:02:11.769 --> 1:02:12.979
[breathing heavily]

1:02:18.317 --> 1:02:20.319
[grunting]

1:02:33.499 --> 1:02:34.709
Closer.

1:02:35.334 --> 1:02:37.336
Boss, you know you ain't
supposed to do that.

1:02:39.005 --> 1:02:40.965
Mind your business, Del.

1:02:50.683 --> 1:02:52.727
What do you want, John Coffey?

1:02:53.686 --> 1:02:54.812
[whispering] Just to help it.

1:02:58.566 --> 1:03:00.026
[Coffey] Don't be afraid.

1:03:00.526 --> 1:03:01.611
Help!

1:03:02.403 --> 1:03:05.156
Help! John Coffey's killing Boss Edgecomb!

1:03:05.364 --> 1:03:06.949
Help!

1:03:07.033 --> 1:03:10.369
-What are you doing?
-[Del] Help!

1:03:12.872 --> 1:03:14.540
Boss Howell! Help!

1:03:15.500 --> 1:03:17.210
-[grunts]
-Boss Stanton! Somebody, come!

1:03:17.543 --> 1:03:19.587
Help!

1:03:21.297 --> 1:03:22.840
[Paul grunting]

1:03:27.512 --> 1:03:28.763
[screams]

1:03:32.558 --> 1:03:35.645
[Del] Help!

1:03:35.728 --> 1:03:38.064
Help! Boss Howell! Boss Stanton!

1:03:38.397 --> 1:03:41.359
Somebody, come!
John Coffey's killing Boss Edgecomb!

1:03:41.442 --> 1:03:43.736
Del, for Christ sakes, shut up!

1:03:44.570 --> 1:03:45.738
[Coffey coughing]

1:04:30.616 --> 1:04:32.743
What did you just do to me?

1:04:34.871 --> 1:04:36.455
I helped it.

1:04:37.623 --> 1:04:39.250
Didn't l help it?

1:04:40.293 --> 1:04:42.128
I just took it back, is all.

1:04:43.462 --> 1:04:45.298
Awful tired now, boss.

1:04:46.465 --> 1:04:47.800
Dog-tired.

1:05:12.325 --> 1:05:15.077
[Del] Boss, what that man do to you?

1:05:38.434 --> 1:05:40.144
[unzipping]

1:05:42.021 --> 1:05:44.357
[urinating]

1:05:55.201 --> 1:05:56.744
[sighs]

1:06:01.082 --> 1:06:02.959
[sighs heavily]

1:06:04.043 --> 1:06:06.212
[soft music playing on radio]

1:06:17.723 --> 1:06:20.226
Hey, honey. How you feeling?

1:06:22.353 --> 1:06:24.563
Oh, not too bad.

1:06:26.273 --> 1:06:27.400
What did the doctor say?

1:06:30.403 --> 1:06:32.196
Oh, you know doctors.

1:06:32.613 --> 1:06:34.407
Gobbledygook, mostly.

1:06:35.491 --> 1:06:36.951
Gobbledygook.

1:06:48.921 --> 1:06:50.464
[clicks tongue]

1:06:52.258 --> 1:06:53.884
Having stew tonight.

1:07:04.061 --> 1:07:05.771
What are you doing?

1:07:12.611 --> 1:07:14.488
What does it feel like?

1:07:15.156 --> 1:07:17.491
Well, l know what it feels like.

1:07:21.454 --> 1:07:23.289
It feels great.

1:07:32.631 --> 1:07:35.134
-[Jan moaning]
-[bed creaking]

1:07:42.600 --> 1:07:45.019
[Paul moaning]

1:07:49.982 --> 1:07:51.275
[Jan] Mmm.

1:07:57.615 --> 1:07:59.325
-Paul.
-Yeah?

1:07:59.950 --> 1:08:02.661
-Not that I'm complaining...
-Uh-huh.

1:08:03.954 --> 1:08:07.416
But we haven't gone four times
in one night since we were 19.

1:08:07.500 --> 1:08:10.169
-Yeah, we did, at your mom's, yeah.
-Mmm-hmm.

1:08:11.670 --> 1:08:13.881
Wanna tell me what's going on?

1:08:13.964 --> 1:08:15.216
[panting]

1:08:17.301 --> 1:08:18.677
Well...

1:08:20.179 --> 1:08:21.972
See, the thing is

1:08:23.516 --> 1:08:26.602
I never actually made it in
to Dr. Bishop's yesterday.

1:08:30.064 --> 1:08:32.525
Brutal, Paul. Listen.

1:08:33.025 --> 1:08:35.694
I'm thinking of taking
the morning off sick.

1:08:35.778 --> 1:08:37.363
You cover the fort for me?

1:08:38.531 --> 1:08:40.866
That's swell. Thanks.

1:08:40.950 --> 1:08:43.786
Yeah, no.
[stammering] I'm sure I'll feel better.

1:08:43.869 --> 1:08:45.788
Okay. Okay.

1:08:51.877 --> 1:08:53.003
You're sure you ought to do this?

1:08:55.506 --> 1:08:57.383
I'm not sure what I'm sure of.

1:09:14.567 --> 1:09:16.986
Burt, you got some company.

1:09:18.237 --> 1:09:19.989
Can l offer you a cold drink?

1:09:20.072 --> 1:09:22.741
Oh, yes, ma'am.
A cold drink would be fine. Thank you.

1:09:23.492 --> 1:09:26.704
Mr. Hammersmith, your office said
I might find you at home today.

1:09:26.787 --> 1:09:28.455
Hope I'm not troubling you.

1:09:29.123 --> 1:09:31.333
Well, that depends, Mr...

1:09:31.417 --> 1:09:35.421
Paul Edgecomb. I'm E Block supervisor
up on Cold Mountain.

1:09:36.714 --> 1:09:38.174
The Green Mile.

1:09:38.257 --> 1:09:41.260
Yeah, I've heard of it.
Lost a few clients your way.

1:09:42.136 --> 1:09:43.846
I'd like to ask you about one of 'em.

1:09:43.929 --> 1:09:45.973
[thunder rumbling]

1:09:46.056 --> 1:09:48.017
-Have a seat.
-Thank you.

1:09:52.688 --> 1:09:53.814
Which client?

1:09:53.898 --> 1:09:55.107
[clears throat]

1:09:56.025 --> 1:09:58.444
Now you got my curiosity aroused.

1:09:59.028 --> 1:10:00.362
John Coffey.

1:10:00.446 --> 1:10:01.447
Ah.

1:10:01.530 --> 1:10:03.073
Coffey.

1:10:03.157 --> 1:10:04.450
He causing you problems?

1:10:04.825 --> 1:10:08.621
No. No, can't say he is. He doesn't like
the dark and cries on occasion.

1:10:08.704 --> 1:10:10.497
But other than that...

1:10:10.581 --> 1:10:13.876
He cries, does he?
Well, got a lot to cry about, I'd say.

1:10:14.168 --> 1:10:15.711
You know what he did.

1:10:16.378 --> 1:10:18.172
I read the court transcript.

1:10:19.590 --> 1:10:21.926
-Thank you, missus.
-My pleasure.

1:10:23.093 --> 1:10:26.096
Kids! Lunch is about ready.
Y'all come on up.

1:10:26.555 --> 1:10:27.806
[both] Coming, Mama!

1:10:27.890 --> 1:10:30.976
What exactly are you trying to find out?

1:10:31.769 --> 1:10:34.104
I've wondered if he ever did
anything like that before.

1:10:35.564 --> 1:10:37.483
Why? Has he said anything?

1:10:37.566 --> 1:10:40.319
No, but a man who does a thing like that

1:10:41.111 --> 1:10:43.280
has often developed
a taste for it over time.

1:10:43.364 --> 1:10:44.240
It occurred to me

1:10:45.157 --> 1:10:48.494
that it might be easy enough
to follow his back trail. Find out.

1:10:49.828 --> 1:10:53.332
A man his size, and colored to boot,
can't be that hard to trace.

1:10:53.832 --> 1:10:57.086
You'd think so, but you'd be wrong.

1:10:57.169 --> 1:10:59.338
Believe me, we tried.

1:11:00.005 --> 1:11:01.507
Like he dropped out of the sky.

1:11:03.008 --> 1:11:04.593
How can that be?

1:11:04.677 --> 1:11:08.430
We're in a depression.
A third of the country's out of work.

1:11:08.973 --> 1:11:13.227
People are drifting by the thousands,
looking for jobs, for that greener grass.

1:11:13.310 --> 1:11:16.355
Even a giant like Coffey
wouldn't get noticed everywhere he goes.

1:11:17.231 --> 1:11:19.525
Not until he kills
a couple of little girls.

1:11:20.401 --> 1:11:21.819
He is, uh,

1:11:22.361 --> 1:11:24.405
strange, l admit.

1:11:24.822 --> 1:11:28.575
But there doesn't seem to be
any real violence in him.

1:11:29.535 --> 1:11:31.996
I know violent men, Mr. Hammersmith.

1:11:32.079 --> 1:11:34.123
I deal with them day in and day out.

1:11:35.874 --> 1:11:38.627
You didn't come up here to ask me
whether he might have killed before.

1:11:38.711 --> 1:11:40.963
You came up here to see
if l think he did it at all.

1:11:43.048 --> 1:11:44.633
-Do you?
-[thunder rumbling]

1:11:45.968 --> 1:11:48.262
One seldom sees a less ambiguous case.

1:11:48.345 --> 1:11:50.472
He was found with the victims in his arms.

1:11:50.556 --> 1:11:52.224
And yet you defended him.

1:11:53.350 --> 1:11:55.394
Everyone is entitled to a defense.

1:11:56.437 --> 1:11:58.230
[Cynthia] Kids! Lunch!

1:11:58.314 --> 1:11:59.606
Y'all listen to your mama now!

1:12:04.153 --> 1:12:06.113
I'll tell you something.

1:12:06.864 --> 1:12:08.991
And you listen close, too,
because it might be something

1:12:09.074 --> 1:12:10.576
you need to know.

1:12:10.659 --> 1:12:12.036
I'm listening.

1:12:13.412 --> 1:12:14.538
We had us a dog.

1:12:15.581 --> 1:12:17.666
Just a sweet mongrel.

1:12:17.750 --> 1:12:19.251
You know the kind.

1:12:20.669 --> 1:12:24.006
Well, in many ways,
a good mongrel dog is like a Negro.

1:12:24.923 --> 1:12:26.633
You get to know it.

1:12:26.967 --> 1:12:31.388
Often, you get to love it.
It is of no particular use,

1:12:31.472 --> 1:12:34.433
but you keep it around
because you think it loves you.

1:12:34.516 --> 1:12:36.143
[chuckles]

1:12:36.518 --> 1:12:40.606
If you're lucky, Mr. Edgecomb,
you never have to find out any different.

1:12:41.732 --> 1:12:43.108
My wife and l were not so lucky.

1:12:45.903 --> 1:12:47.446
Caleb, come here for a second.

1:12:48.781 --> 1:12:50.115
Come here.

1:12:51.450 --> 1:12:52.659
Please, son.

1:12:54.286 --> 1:12:56.163
He still has the one good eye.

1:12:58.123 --> 1:13:00.459
I suppose he's lucky

1:13:00.542 --> 1:13:02.628
not to be completely blind.

1:13:05.672 --> 1:13:09.176
We get down on our knees
and thank God for that much at least.

1:13:10.052 --> 1:13:11.512
Right, Caleb?

1:13:13.972 --> 1:13:15.307
Okay, go on in now.

1:13:16.058 --> 1:13:17.559
[door opening]

1:13:17.643 --> 1:13:18.727
[door closing]

1:13:18.811 --> 1:13:21.480
That dog attacked my boy for no reason.

1:13:22.314 --> 1:13:24.316
Just got it in his mind one day.

1:13:25.234 --> 1:13:26.860
The same with John Coffey.

1:13:26.944 --> 1:13:31.115
He was sorry afterwards.
Of that l have no doubt.

1:13:31.824 --> 1:13:36.120
But those little girls
stayed raped and murdered.

1:13:36.995 --> 1:13:38.997
Maybe he'd never done it before.

1:13:40.791 --> 1:13:42.751
My dog never bit before.

1:13:44.670 --> 1:13:47.339
But l didn't concern myself with that.

1:13:48.424 --> 1:13:50.217
I went out there with my rifle

1:13:50.300 --> 1:13:52.302
and grabbed his collar
and blew his brains out.

1:13:53.762 --> 1:13:54.888
Is Coffey guilty?

1:13:57.891 --> 1:13:59.601
Yes, he is.

1:14:00.144 --> 1:14:01.145
Don't you doubt it.

