1:34:15.149 --> 1:34:17.193
You're no better at mouse-killing
than you are at...

1:34:18.069 --> 1:34:19.862
Hell, at anything else around here.

1:34:20.321 --> 1:34:21.572
[scoffs]

1:34:22.448 --> 1:34:24.742
[Percy] Yeah,
you expect me to believe that? Huh?

1:34:25.368 --> 1:34:26.535
[chuckling]

1:34:26.619 --> 1:34:28.704
I heard the goddamn thing crunch.

1:34:29.372 --> 1:34:31.457
Aren't you glad Mr. Jingles is okay?

1:34:32.792 --> 1:34:34.543
After all those talks we had about

1:34:35.503 --> 1:34:36.962
keeping the prisoners calm?

1:34:37.797 --> 1:34:39.048
Aren't you relieved?

1:34:39.632 --> 1:34:41.008
What kind of game is this?

1:34:41.092 --> 1:34:42.218
It's no game.

1:34:42.968 --> 1:34:44.261
See for yourself.

1:34:47.431 --> 1:34:48.599
Go on.

1:34:58.234 --> 1:35:00.653
[Del speaking indistinctly]

1:35:01.987 --> 1:35:04.240
Don't let nothing happen to Mr. Jingle.

1:35:05.950 --> 1:35:07.827
[footsteps approaching]

1:35:09.120 --> 1:35:10.538
You switched him.

1:35:10.621 --> 1:35:12.456
You switched him somehow, you bastards.

1:35:13.290 --> 1:35:17.420
I always keep a spare mouse in my wallet
for occasions such as this.

1:35:17.503 --> 1:35:20.506
Oh, yeah, you playing with me, huh?
Both of you.

1:35:20.589 --> 1:35:22.633
Just who the hell you think you are, huh?

1:35:22.716 --> 1:35:23.759
Ah!

1:35:25.886 --> 1:35:27.513
[Paul] We're the people
you work with, Percy.

1:35:28.055 --> 1:35:29.348
But not for long.

1:35:29.974 --> 1:35:32.143
-[grunts]
-Percy, I want your word.

1:35:33.269 --> 1:35:34.270
My word?

1:35:34.895 --> 1:35:37.148
I put you out front for Del,

1:35:38.399 --> 1:35:41.569
you put in your transfer
to Briar Ridge the very next day.

1:35:42.611 --> 1:35:46.323
Well, what if I just call up
certain people

1:35:46.824 --> 1:35:48.242
and tell 'em you're harassing me?

1:35:48.993 --> 1:35:51.120
-Bullying me.
-[Paul] Go ahead.

1:35:51.912 --> 1:35:54.832
I promise you'll leave your share
of blood on the floor.

1:35:55.332 --> 1:35:57.501
-Over a mouse?
-No!

1:35:58.461 --> 1:36:00.588
But four men will swear you stood by

1:36:01.130 --> 1:36:03.090
while Wild Bill
tried to strangle Dean to death.

1:36:03.174 --> 1:36:05.509
About that, people will care.
Even your uncle, the governor,

1:36:06.218 --> 1:36:07.261
will care about that.

1:36:07.344 --> 1:36:09.305
Thing like that goes on your work record.

1:36:10.347 --> 1:36:14.310
Work record can follow a man around
for a long, long time.

1:36:14.810 --> 1:36:16.353
[Paul] I put you out front,

1:36:17.062 --> 1:36:18.939
you put in for that transfer.

1:36:21.025 --> 1:36:22.276
That's the deal.

1:36:26.489 --> 1:36:27.823
All right.

1:36:29.241 --> 1:36:30.367
All right.

1:36:37.541 --> 1:36:39.793
You make a promise to a man,
you shake his hand.

1:36:54.433 --> 1:36:56.101
[thunder rumbling]

1:36:57.478 --> 1:36:59.063
[rain pattering]

1:37:03.359 --> 1:37:06.111
[lightning cracking]

1:37:42.439 --> 1:37:43.774
Hey, boys.

1:37:45.442 --> 1:37:48.153
No, now, say, "Hey," Mr. Jingles.

1:37:50.948 --> 1:37:52.950
[Paul] Eduard Delacroix,
will you step forward?

1:37:55.077 --> 1:37:56.412
[thunder rumbling]

1:38:08.048 --> 1:38:09.216
Boss Edgecomb?

1:38:09.967 --> 1:38:11.260
Yes, Del?

1:38:11.677 --> 1:38:14.054
Don't let nothing happen
to Mr. Jingle, okay?

1:38:15.806 --> 1:38:17.891
Here. You take him.

1:38:23.814 --> 1:38:24.982
Del,

1:38:27.318 --> 1:38:29.903
I can't have a mouse
on my shoulder while...

1:38:31.655 --> 1:38:32.948
You know.

1:38:35.075 --> 1:38:36.285
[Coffey] I'll take him, boss.

1:38:37.411 --> 1:38:39.747
Just for now, if Del don't mind.

1:38:42.875 --> 1:38:44.001
Yeah.

1:38:44.752 --> 1:38:46.253
Yeah, you take him, John.

1:38:46.337 --> 1:38:48.631
You take him
till this foolishment be done.

1:39:10.319 --> 1:39:12.237
You gonna take him to Florida,
to that Mouseville?

1:39:13.197 --> 1:39:14.865
We'll do it together, most likely.

1:39:16.700 --> 1:39:18.285
Maybe take a little vacation time.

1:39:19.036 --> 1:39:20.120
Yeah.

1:39:20.204 --> 1:39:22.373
People pay a dime apiece to see him.

1:39:23.374 --> 1:39:25.125
Two cents for the kids.

1:39:25.209 --> 1:39:26.210
Ain't that right, Boss Howell?

1:39:26.293 --> 1:39:27.628
That's right, Del.

1:39:30.255 --> 1:39:31.924
You're a good man, Boss Howell.

1:39:35.594 --> 1:39:36.929
You, too, Boss Edgecomb.

1:39:41.183 --> 1:39:43.852
I sure wish I could've met you guys
somewheres else.

1:39:49.566 --> 1:39:52.444
[speaking French]

1:40:05.958 --> 1:40:07.626
[thunder rumbling]

1:40:23.517 --> 1:40:25.644
Hope he's good and scared.

1:40:25.728 --> 1:40:27.813
Hope he knows the fires are stoked

1:40:27.896 --> 1:40:29.690
and that Satan's imps are waiting.

1:40:39.700 --> 1:40:41.118
Del, it's all right.

1:41:04.224 --> 1:41:05.559
[thunder rumbling]

1:41:24.369 --> 1:41:25.496
Roll on one.

1:41:26.872 --> 1:41:28.373
[electricity humming]

1:41:28.499 --> 1:41:29.833
[whirring]

1:41:37.174 --> 1:41:39.551
[whispering] You be still, Mr. Jingles.

1:41:41.428 --> 1:41:44.348
You be so quiet and so still.

1:41:44.681 --> 1:41:46.141
[lightning cracking]

1:41:48.519 --> 1:41:50.062
Eduard Delacroix,

1:41:50.479 --> 1:41:53.524
you've been condemned to die
by a jury of your peers,

1:41:54.024 --> 1:41:57.736
sentence imposed by a judge
in good standing in this state.

1:41:58.237 --> 1:42:01.156
You have anything to say
before sentence is carried out?

1:42:04.701 --> 1:42:06.328
[sobbing]

1:42:06.829 --> 1:42:08.163
[sniffles]

1:42:09.665 --> 1:42:11.458
I sorry for what I...

1:42:18.799 --> 1:42:20.676
I sorry for what I do.

1:42:21.510 --> 1:42:23.512
I give anything to take it back.

1:42:24.972 --> 1:42:26.390
But I can't.

1:42:27.808 --> 1:42:29.601
God have mercy on me.

1:42:30.727 --> 1:42:32.604
[speaking French] Amen.

1:42:41.321 --> 1:42:42.906
Don't forget about Mouseville.

1:42:45.784 --> 1:42:46.869
Hey,

1:42:48.245 --> 1:42:49.621
there's no such place.

1:42:50.581 --> 1:42:53.584
That's just a fairy tale
these guys told you to keep you quiet.

1:42:54.418 --> 1:42:55.669
[sobbing]

1:42:56.879 --> 1:42:59.464
Just thought you should know, faggot.

1:42:59.548 --> 1:43:01.049
[Del sniffles]

1:43:04.428 --> 1:43:05.846
[lightning cracking]

1:43:13.812 --> 1:43:16.732
[Del praying in French]

1:43:28.952 --> 1:43:31.121
[continues praying in French]

1:43:53.727 --> 1:43:54.770
[clears throat]

1:43:54.978 --> 1:43:56.647
[thunder rumbling]

1:44:01.526 --> 1:44:02.986
Eduard Delacroix,

1:44:03.487 --> 1:44:05.989
electricity shall now be
passed through your body

1:44:06.073 --> 1:44:09.159
until you are dead
in accordance with state law.

1:44:10.994 --> 1:44:13.163
God have mercy on your soul.

1:44:22.714 --> 1:44:24.341
[sobbing]

1:44:27.010 --> 1:44:28.637
[ticking]

1:44:52.327 --> 1:44:53.370
Roll on two!

1:44:54.746 --> 1:44:55.872
[muffled grunting]

1:44:59.126 --> 1:45:00.961
[whooping]

1:45:02.879 --> 1:45:04.214
[screaming]

1:45:10.637 --> 1:45:11.847
[whispers] The sponge is dry.

1:45:12.222 --> 1:45:13.348
What?

1:45:15.225 --> 1:45:17.019
[screaming continues]

1:45:18.729 --> 1:45:20.814
Jack, the goddamn sponge is dry!

1:45:20.897 --> 1:45:22.315
Well, don't you stop it!

1:45:22.399 --> 1:45:24.276
Don't you do it! It's too late for that.

1:45:24.359 --> 1:45:25.736
[screaming]

1:45:40.083 --> 1:45:41.793
Is this normal?

1:45:41.877 --> 1:45:44.004
God, the smell.

1:45:44.087 --> 1:45:45.130
Oh.

1:45:45.756 --> 1:45:47.090
He's cooking now!

1:45:47.174 --> 1:45:48.425
They cooking him good!

1:45:48.884 --> 1:45:50.594
They're about done, I reckon!

1:45:50.927 --> 1:45:52.637
[whooping]

1:45:52.721 --> 1:45:53.889
[exclaims]

1:45:53.972 --> 1:45:55.182
[Wharton] Yeah!

1:45:55.265 --> 1:45:57.392
We're gonna have a hoedown!

1:45:58.560 --> 1:46:00.187
[continues whooping]

1:46:00.270 --> 1:46:02.105
[screaming]

1:46:02.189 --> 1:46:04.816
-[Wharton] Yeah! He's cooking now!
-[crying]

1:46:04.900 --> 1:46:06.610
He's cooking now!

1:46:07.152 --> 1:46:10.781
We gonna have a hoedown! 'Cution gumbo.

1:46:11.406 --> 1:46:12.949
-Give me some!
-[screaming]

1:46:13.617 --> 1:46:16.328
Give me some! I'm smelling gumbo!

1:46:16.787 --> 1:46:19.706
I'm smelling... I said, give me some!

1:46:24.086 --> 1:46:25.462
I smell it!

1:46:27.506 --> 1:46:29.049
-[screaming]
-[Wharton] I smell it!

1:46:29.341 --> 1:46:30.550
-[screaming]
-[whirring]

1:46:36.973 --> 1:46:38.058
Should I kill the juice?

1:46:38.141 --> 1:46:39.768
No! Roll, for chrisssake, roll!

1:46:48.693 --> 1:46:50.946
[all clamoring]

1:47:03.250 --> 1:47:06.211
He's frying now! He's frying now!

1:47:06.586 --> 1:47:08.088
He's frying now!

1:47:09.673 --> 1:47:12.425
-Why don't you shut it down?
-He's still alive.

1:47:12.509 --> 1:47:14.344
You want me to shut down
while he's still alive?

1:47:20.851 --> 1:47:23.103
You watch, you son of a bitch!

1:47:24.855 --> 1:47:27.566
It's all right, folks!
It's all under control!

1:47:28.316 --> 1:47:31.027
Everybody stay calm! Please, stay calm!

1:47:36.825 --> 1:47:37.868
Kill it!

1:47:40.370 --> 1:47:41.538
[machine stops]

1:47:44.875 --> 1:47:45.917
You do it!

1:47:46.001 --> 1:47:47.544
You're running this show, ain't you?

1:47:48.712 --> 1:47:50.547
[clamoring continues]

1:48:15.906 --> 1:48:18.408
I didn't know the sponge
is supposed to be wet.

1:48:19.492 --> 1:48:20.869
-[exclaims]
-[Paul] Brutal!

1:48:21.661 --> 1:48:23.079
Brutal, no!

1:48:23.163 --> 1:48:25.332
-No! No!
-What do you mean, "No"?

1:48:25.415 --> 1:48:27.209
How can you say no? You saw what he did!

1:48:27.292 --> 1:48:28.335
Delacroix's dead!

1:48:28.418 --> 1:48:30.420
Now, there's nothing can change that,
and Percy is not worth it!

1:48:30.503 --> 1:48:32.756
So he just gets away with it?
Is that how it works?

1:48:33.215 --> 1:48:35.091
[footsteps approaching]

1:48:41.598 --> 1:48:44.100
What in the blue fuck was that?

1:48:45.936 --> 1:48:47.479
Jesus Christ.

1:48:47.562 --> 1:48:49.648
There's puke all over the floor up there.

1:48:50.440 --> 1:48:51.942
And the smell.

1:48:52.943 --> 1:48:54.694
I got Van Hay to open both doors,

1:48:54.778 --> 1:48:56.947
but that smell won't go out
for five damn years.

1:48:57.030 --> 1:48:58.365
That's what I'm betting.

1:48:59.616 --> 1:49:02.285
And that asshole Wharton
is singing about it!

1:49:03.453 --> 1:49:04.871
You can hear him up there!

1:49:05.497 --> 1:49:07.499
Can he carry a tune, Hal?

1:49:11.962 --> 1:49:13.630
[chuckles]

1:49:18.885 --> 1:49:20.512
Okay, boys, okay.

1:49:21.513 --> 1:49:24.474
Now, what in the hell happened?

1:49:24.766 --> 1:49:25.892
An execution.

1:49:26.476 --> 1:49:27.811
A successful one.

1:49:28.144 --> 1:49:32.065
How in the name of Christ
can you call that a success?

1:49:33.066 --> 1:49:35.151
Eduard Delacroix is dead.

1:49:36.820 --> 1:49:38.113
Isn't he?

1:49:42.617 --> 1:49:44.411
-Percy?
-Yeah.

1:49:45.161 --> 1:49:46.454
Something to say?

1:49:50.333 --> 1:49:52.836
I didn't know the sponge
is supposed to be wet.

1:49:54.254 --> 1:49:56.965
How many years you spend
pissing on a toilet seat

1:49:57.173 --> 1:49:58.925
before someone told you to put it up?

1:49:59.009 --> 1:50:00.844
Percy fucked up, Hal.

1:50:01.469 --> 1:50:02.721
Pure and simple.

1:50:03.513 --> 1:50:05.598
That's your official position?

1:50:05.682 --> 1:50:07.017
Don't you think it should be?

1:50:08.018 --> 1:50:11.062
He's putting in for a transfer request
to Briar Ridge tomorrow.

1:50:12.188 --> 1:50:14.065
Moving on to bigger and better things.

1:50:15.025 --> 1:50:16.109
Isn't that right, Percy?

1:50:18.028 --> 1:50:19.446
Yeah. Yeah.

1:50:19.571 --> 1:50:22.782
[Wharton singing]
<i>Barbecue. Me and you</i>

1:50:22.866 --> 1:50:24.326
<i>Stinky, pinky</i>

1:50:24.409 --> 1:50:25.994
[scatting]

1:50:26.077 --> 1:50:29.247
<i>Weren't Billy, Jilly, Hilly or Pa</i>

1:50:29.331 --> 1:50:32.751
<i>It was a French-fried Cajun</i>
<i>Named Delacroix</i>

1:50:32.834 --> 1:50:33.918
Whoo!

1:50:34.002 --> 1:50:37.464
<i>Barbecue, me and you</i>

1:50:37.547 --> 1:50:40.717
<i>Stinky, pinky</i>
<i>Phew, phew, phew</i>

1:50:41.134 --> 1:50:42.552
<i>Weren't Billy, Jilly...</i>

1:50:43.678 --> 1:50:45.096
You're about ten seconds away

1:50:45.180 --> 1:50:47.098
from spending the rest of your life
in the padded room.

1:50:56.775 --> 1:50:58.443
[thunder rumbling]

1:51:04.574 --> 1:51:06.076
[sobbing]

1:51:06.159 --> 1:51:07.285
Poor old Del.

1:51:08.953 --> 1:51:10.080
Yeah.

1:51:11.039 --> 1:51:12.499
Poor old Del.

1:51:15.001 --> 1:51:16.086
John?

1:51:18.755 --> 1:51:20.006
You okay?

1:51:21.466 --> 1:51:23.510
I could feel it from here.

1:51:24.344 --> 1:51:25.970
What do you mean?

1:51:26.638 --> 1:51:27.806
You could hear it.

1:51:28.473 --> 1:51:30.016
Is that what you mean?

1:51:30.100 --> 1:51:33.103
-You could hear it.
-He out of it now, though.

1:51:33.770 --> 1:51:35.105
He the lucky one.

1:51:36.147 --> 1:51:38.191
No matter how it happened,

1:51:38.274 --> 1:51:39.943
Del the lucky one.

1:51:41.277 --> 1:51:42.445
[sobs]

1:51:46.533 --> 1:51:48.284
Where's Mr. Jingles?

1:51:49.661 --> 1:51:51.788
He run away under that door.

1:51:53.540 --> 1:51:55.583
Don't think he'll be back.

1:51:57.168 --> 1:51:59.629
He felt it too, through me.

1:52:01.172 --> 1:52:03.383
Didn't mean to hurt him none.

1:52:03.925 --> 1:52:06.469
All that hurt just spill out.

1:52:09.139 --> 1:52:10.390
[sniffles]

1:52:10.473 --> 1:52:11.641
[sighs]

1:52:13.643 --> 1:52:15.520
Awful tired now, boss.

1:52:17.814 --> 1:52:19.149
Dog-tired.

1:52:25.280 --> 1:52:27.115
[softly] Me too, John.

1:52:27.198 --> 1:52:29.492
[Coffey sobbing softly]

1:52:29.576 --> 1:52:30.827
Me, too.

1:52:44.674 --> 1:52:46.843
[jazz music playing on radio]

1:53:29.093 --> 1:53:30.845
-[turns off engine]
-[sighs]

1:53:30.929 --> 1:53:32.347
I hate this.

1:53:33.264 --> 1:53:34.474
I know.

1:53:49.572 --> 1:53:51.991
[Jan] Melinda, hi.

1:53:56.246 --> 1:53:58.498
-I am so happy to see you.
-Oh.

1:53:59.958 --> 1:54:01.376
Look at you.

1:54:02.710 --> 1:54:04.587
Well, we missed you at church.

1:54:07.090 --> 1:54:08.424
Oh!

1:54:08.508 --> 1:54:10.426
Ah, my hair.

1:54:11.094 --> 1:54:12.178
You look fine.

1:54:12.262 --> 1:54:13.846
I'm just a mess.

1:54:16.766 --> 1:54:18.101
[sizzling]

1:54:19.310 --> 1:54:21.771
She's having one of her good days.

1:54:22.355 --> 1:54:24.148
I thank God for that.

1:54:26.609 --> 1:54:28.278
What's a bad day?

1:54:31.864 --> 1:54:33.533
Sometimes she's...

1:54:35.118 --> 1:54:36.494
She's not herself anymore.

1:54:37.120 --> 1:54:38.454
She swears.

1:54:38.955 --> 1:54:40.290
She swears?

1:54:40.373 --> 1:54:42.000
It just pops out.

1:54:42.792 --> 1:54:44.836
Most awful language you can imagine.

1:54:45.545 --> 1:54:47.630
She doesn't even know she's doing it.

1:54:49.257 --> 1:54:51.342
I didn't know
she'd ever heard words like that.

1:54:52.260 --> 1:54:54.971
To hear her say them in her sweet voice.

1:54:59.809 --> 1:55:01.603
I'm glad she's having a good day, Paul.

1:55:03.438 --> 1:55:05.440
I'm glad for you and Jan.

1:55:21.789 --> 1:55:23.082
Honey,

1:55:23.166 --> 1:55:25.919
if you don't tell me what's on your mind,

1:55:26.586 --> 1:55:29.172
I'm afraid I'll have to
smother you with a pillow.

1:55:38.848 --> 1:55:40.642
I'm thinking I love you.

1:55:42.894 --> 1:55:45.605
I'm thinking I don't know
what I would do if you were gone.

1:55:48.441 --> 1:55:49.484
Oh.

1:55:52.612 --> 1:55:55.615
I'm also thinking I'm gonna
have the boys over tomorrow.

1:56:00.203 --> 1:56:02.956
Well, you sure do know
how to cook chicken.

1:56:03.039 --> 1:56:04.457
Well, thank you.

1:56:04.540 --> 1:56:07.335
This is one delicious treat, ma'am,
before I go to work.

1:56:07.418 --> 1:56:08.962
Well, I'm glad you're enjoying it.

1:56:09.462 --> 1:56:10.630
-Hey, Brutal.
-Hmm.

1:56:10.713 --> 1:56:11.881
You gonna hog all them taters?

1:56:11.965 --> 1:56:13.132
Yes, I am.

1:56:13.883 --> 1:56:15.760
-Harry, you want some taters?
-Come on, now.

1:56:16.052 --> 1:56:17.095
What?

1:56:17.178 --> 1:56:19.973
[Jan] Very soon we'll just see your feet
sticking out of there, Brutus.

1:56:20.056 --> 1:56:21.557
Y'all saw what he did to the mouse.

1:56:25.353 --> 1:56:27.647
I could've gone the rest of the day
without you bringing that up.

1:56:27.730 --> 1:56:29.399
I could've gone the rest of the year.

1:56:29.983 --> 1:56:31.484
He did the same thing to me.

1:56:32.276 --> 1:56:33.861
He put his hands on me.

1:56:35.196 --> 1:56:36.906
He took my bladder infection away.

1:56:42.078 --> 1:56:45.164
It's true.
When he came home that day, he was

1:56:47.125 --> 1:56:48.626
all better.

1:56:50.003 --> 1:56:54.173
Oh, now, wait. You're talking about
an authentic healing?

1:56:56.217 --> 1:56:57.635
A praise-Jesus miracle?

1:56:58.594 --> 1:56:59.595
I am.

1:57:00.471 --> 1:57:01.597
Oh, yeah.

1:57:02.098 --> 1:57:04.600
Well, if you say it, I accept it.

1:57:06.185 --> 1:57:07.437
What's it got to do with us?

1:57:08.479 --> 1:57:09.772
You're thinking about Melinda.

1:57:10.273 --> 1:57:11.315
Melinda?

1:57:12.275 --> 1:57:15.028
-Melinda Moores?
-Yeah. So, Paul,

1:57:15.111 --> 1:57:16.821
you really think you can help her?

1:57:17.613 --> 1:57:19.198
It's not a bladder infection

1:57:19.574 --> 1:57:21.451
or even a busted mouse,

1:57:22.869 --> 1:57:23.995
but I think there might be a chance.

1:57:24.412 --> 1:57:25.872
Hold on now.

1:57:25.955 --> 1:57:27.957
You're talking about our jobs.

1:57:28.041 --> 1:57:30.334
Sneak a sick woman into a cellblock?

1:57:30.418 --> 1:57:32.462
Oh, no. No, no.
Hal would never stand for that.

1:57:33.504 --> 1:57:34.422
You know him.

1:57:34.505 --> 1:57:36.132
He wouldn't believe anything
even if it fell on him.

1:57:36.215 --> 1:57:37.467
So you're talking about

1:57:38.426 --> 1:57:39.844
taking John Coffey to her.

1:57:45.641 --> 1:57:47.643
That's more than just our jobs, Paul.

1:57:49.020 --> 1:57:50.480
That's prison time, we get caught.

1:57:50.563 --> 1:57:51.898
You're dang right, it is.

1:57:51.981 --> 1:57:53.858
[Paul] No, not for you, Dean.

1:57:53.941 --> 1:57:57.195
See now, the way I figure it,
you stay back on the Mile.

1:57:57.278 --> 1:57:58.780
That way, you can deny everything.

1:57:59.739 --> 1:58:01.115
Why do I have to stay behind?

1:58:02.033 --> 1:58:04.786
Well, our boy's grown up,

1:58:05.411 --> 1:58:06.913
gone off to school.

1:58:06.996 --> 1:58:09.082
Harry's girls, they're all married now.

1:58:09.957 --> 1:58:11.042
Brutal's a single man.

1:58:11.125 --> 1:58:14.337
You're the only one here
with two children, another one on the way.

1:58:15.171 --> 1:58:18.091
Let's not discuss this
as if we're thinking of doing it.

1:58:20.510 --> 1:58:22.762
Brutal, help me out here.

1:58:24.514 --> 1:58:27.683
-I'm sure she's a fine woman.
-The finest.

1:58:28.101 --> 1:58:30.603
What is happening to her
is an offense, Brutal.

1:58:30.686 --> 1:58:33.147
To the eye and the ear and to the heart.

1:58:33.231 --> 1:58:34.857
I have no doubt.

1:58:36.400 --> 1:58:38.486
But we don't know her
like you and Jan do, do we?

1:58:38.820 --> 1:58:41.572
And let's not forget,
John Coffey is a murderer.

1:58:43.074 --> 1:58:44.659
Now, what if he escapes?

1:58:45.201 --> 1:58:48.121
I'd hate to lose my job or go to prison,

1:58:48.830 --> 1:58:52.041
but I'd hate worse to have
a dead child on my conscience.

1:58:52.125 --> 1:58:53.417
I don't think that's gonna happen.

1:58:55.795 --> 1:58:57.046
In fact,

1:58:59.590 --> 1:59:01.259
I don't think he did it at all.

1:59:04.720 --> 1:59:06.097
I do not see

1:59:06.681 --> 1:59:10.601
God putting a gift like that
in the hands of a man who'd kill a child.

1:59:11.102 --> 1:59:14.772
Well, that's a very tender notion,
but the man is on death row for the crime.

1:59:17.275 --> 1:59:18.317
And plus,

1:59:18.734 --> 1:59:20.403
he's huge.

1:59:20.903 --> 1:59:22.572
If he tried to get away,

1:59:24.198 --> 1:59:25.616
it'd take a lot of bullets to stop him.

1:59:26.033 --> 1:59:27.618
Oh, we'd all have shotguns,

1:59:28.035 --> 1:59:29.495
in addition to side arms.

1:59:30.538 --> 1:59:31.747
I'd insist on that.

1:59:33.082 --> 1:59:35.877
If he tried anything, anything at all,

1:59:36.419 --> 1:59:37.920
we'd have to take him down.

1:59:39.005 --> 1:59:40.006
You understand?

1:59:51.934 --> 1:59:53.060
So,

1:59:53.936 --> 1:59:55.188
tell us what you had in mind.

2:00:02.945 --> 2:00:04.989
[Paul] Oh, there it is.
[Brutal] Oh, I see it.

2:00:05.072 --> 2:00:07.158
[cabinet door opens]

2:00:16.417 --> 2:00:18.085
You think this is enough?

2:00:19.587 --> 2:00:21.047
I don't know.

2:00:57.875 --> 2:00:59.752
You fellas thirsty?

2:00:59.835 --> 2:01:01.504
Fresh out of the icebox.

2:01:01.587 --> 2:01:03.923
You bet. That's swell, Brutal. Thanks.

2:01:04.006 --> 2:01:05.299
[Brutal] Oh, yeah.

2:01:05.383 --> 2:01:07.718
[Harry] Hot in here. Boy, howdy.

2:01:07.802 --> 2:01:10.680
Hey, hey.
I'm gonna get some, too, ain't I?

2:01:11.180 --> 2:01:12.848
My ass, you get some, too.

2:01:12.932 --> 2:01:14.517
What makes you think you deserve any?

2:01:15.351 --> 2:01:17.144
Because I got a big pecker.

2:01:17.728 --> 2:01:20.106
Well, the day report says he's been okay.

2:01:20.898 --> 2:01:23.484
[Wharton] Hell, yeah, I been behaved.
Come on, now.

2:01:23.943 --> 2:01:25.278
Don't be stingy hogs.

2:01:28.531 --> 2:01:29.657
[Wharton] Come on.

2:01:30.491 --> 2:01:32.702
Come on. Come on now, fellers.

2:01:34.245 --> 2:01:35.538
Come on, boss.

2:01:35.871 --> 2:01:37.665
I been good all day.

2:01:40.793 --> 2:01:42.211
It's hot in here.

2:01:42.753 --> 2:01:45.881
It's hot in this cell,
and I'm dogged to drink. I'm thirsty.

2:01:46.382 --> 2:01:48.175
Why don't you give me some?

2:01:55.057 --> 2:01:56.267
Come on.

2:02:01.564 --> 2:02:02.732
You gonna stay behaved?

2:02:03.607 --> 2:02:05.192
Come on, you clunk, give me that.

2:02:05.443 --> 2:02:06.652
You promise me,

2:02:07.528 --> 2:02:09.405
or else I'll drink this myself
right here in front of you.

2:02:09.822 --> 2:02:12.283
Don't, don't, don't...
Come on, now. Don't be that way.

2:02:13.075 --> 2:02:14.201
I'll be good.

2:02:34.180 --> 2:02:35.514
[belching]

2:02:39.393 --> 2:02:40.436
Cup.

2:03:20.976 --> 2:03:22.853
[footsteps approaching]

2:03:31.320 --> 2:03:33.406
Anybody wants out, now's the time.

2:03:34.490 --> 2:03:35.991
After this, there's no turning back.

2:03:37.827 --> 2:03:38.828
So?

2:03:39.995 --> 2:03:41.497
We gonna do this?

2:03:41.580 --> 2:03:44.333
[Coffey] Sure. That'd be just fine.

2:03:44.834 --> 2:03:46.460
I'd like to take a ride.

2:03:52.216 --> 2:03:53.717
Guess we're all in.

2:04:05.521 --> 2:04:06.647
What is this?

2:04:09.066 --> 2:04:10.151
Payback.

2:04:10.484 --> 2:04:11.527
[Brutal] That's right.

2:04:13.237 --> 2:04:14.572
[grunting]

2:04:16.532 --> 2:04:17.950
No, you let me go!

2:04:18.033 --> 2:04:19.452
-Let go of me!
-Settle down.

2:04:19.535 --> 2:04:20.703
-Let go!
-Settle down.

2:04:20.786 --> 2:04:22.496
-What are you doing?
-Settle down.

2:04:29.545 --> 2:04:30.754
Oh!

2:04:31.380 --> 2:04:33.924
-"Miss Lotta Leadpipe."
-[Brutal] Oh, Percy.

2:04:34.258 --> 2:04:35.426
What would your mother say?

2:04:35.509 --> 2:04:37.636
You let go of me, you ignoramus.

2:04:37.720 --> 2:04:40.556
I know people. Big people!

2:04:40.973 --> 2:04:43.726
Percy, stick out your arms
like a good lad.

2:04:44.101 --> 2:04:46.479
No, I won't do it. You can't make me.

2:04:46.562 --> 2:04:48.314
Oh, you're dead wrong about that,
you know.

2:04:49.231 --> 2:04:50.524
[screaming]

2:04:54.737 --> 2:04:57.072
You gonna put your arms up, huh?

2:04:57.865 --> 2:05:01.035
A big man is ripping your ears off, Percy.
I'd do as he says.

2:05:01.118 --> 2:05:02.828
[screaming]

2:05:03.162 --> 2:05:04.413
There you go.

2:05:08.626 --> 2:05:10.252
[panting]

2:05:13.130 --> 2:05:14.298
Please, Paul.

2:05:14.798 --> 2:05:16.926
Please don't put me in with Wild Bill.

2:05:17.009 --> 2:05:18.469
Please don't.

2:05:19.678 --> 2:05:21.013
You would think that.

2:05:23.474 --> 2:05:25.935
No, no, no, you can't do this to me.

2:05:26.018 --> 2:05:28.521
You can't do this to me. You can't.

2:05:29.063 --> 2:05:31.106
I'm gonna let you in
on a little secret, Percy.

2:05:31.190 --> 2:05:33.359
We can and we are.

2:05:33.442 --> 2:05:35.110
[muffled sobbing]

2:05:40.950 --> 2:05:42.701
We'll give you a few hours
of quiet time, Percy,

2:05:42.785 --> 2:05:45.871
so you can reflect on what you did to Del.

2:05:45.955 --> 2:05:49.041
And if you get lonely,
just think about Miss Leadpipe.

2:05:51.168 --> 2:05:52.962
[muffled protesting]

2:05:58.551 --> 2:06:00.803
All right, let's go over it one more time.

2:06:00.886 --> 2:06:02.596
What do you say if somebody stops by?

2:06:04.848 --> 2:06:06.559
Coffey got upset just after lights out,

2:06:06.642 --> 2:06:09.436
so we put the coat on him,
locked him in the restraint room.

2:06:10.312 --> 2:06:12.273
They hear any kicking and fussing,
they'll think it's him.

2:06:12.356 --> 2:06:13.440
What about me?

2:06:13.524 --> 2:06:15.359
You're down in Admin pulling Del's file,

2:06:15.442 --> 2:06:18.821
going over the witnesses on account of
how big a screw-up the execution was.

2:06:21.824 --> 2:06:23.409
We going for the ride now?

2:06:23.826 --> 2:06:25.661
That's right. We going for the ride.

2:06:28.455 --> 2:06:30.124
What about us, Dean?

2:06:30.207 --> 2:06:34.086
You, Harry, Percy, all down in the laundry
doing your wash.

2:06:34.169 --> 2:06:35.921
Probably take y'all a few hours
before you're back.

2:06:36.880 --> 2:06:38.340
[gasping]

2:06:40.342 --> 2:06:41.719
Where you think you going?

2:06:42.344 --> 2:06:43.637
[sobbing]

2:06:48.767 --> 2:06:50.269
You a bad man.

2:06:50.644 --> 2:06:52.855
That's right, nigger. Bad as you'd want.

2:06:52.938 --> 2:06:55.316
[Coffey breathing heavily]

2:07:00.654 --> 2:07:03.824
What's wrong? What's wrong? What's wrong?

2:07:03.907 --> 2:07:05.576
[Wharton laughing]

2:07:20.466 --> 2:07:22.051
[exhales]

2:07:24.386 --> 2:07:25.721
[whooping]

2:07:28.223 --> 2:07:30.726
Whole room... Whole room's spinning.

2:07:31.685 --> 2:07:33.479
It's like I'm shitty-ass drunk.

2:07:34.063 --> 2:07:35.939
Had me some shine or...

2:07:37.191 --> 2:07:38.400
Or what?

2:07:40.903 --> 2:07:43.656
Niggers ought to have
their own electric chair.

2:07:43.739 --> 2:07:44.948
White man

2:07:45.574 --> 2:07:48.118
ought not to have to sit
in no nigger electric chair.

2:07:48.952 --> 2:07:50.204
No, sir.

2:07:52.539 --> 2:07:53.791
[snoring]

2:07:57.378 --> 2:07:59.463
He a bad man.

2:08:01.423 --> 2:08:02.925
[door opening]

2:08:19.650 --> 2:08:20.776
Look, boss.

2:08:25.280 --> 2:08:27.950
It's Cassie,
the lady in the rocking chair.

2:08:28.033 --> 2:08:30.494
[whispering] Shh! John,
we have to be quiet now.

2:08:31.120 --> 2:08:33.497
[whispering] You see her?
You see the lady?

2:08:33.580 --> 2:08:35.290
[Brutal] Yeah, we see her, John. Come on.

2:08:47.302 --> 2:08:49.221
[Paul] Let's go. Go, go!

2:08:53.392 --> 2:08:54.685
Now!

2:09:12.286 --> 2:09:13.912
[inhales]

2:09:30.679 --> 2:09:32.806
All right, big boy.
Let's get moving. Come on.

2:10:07.341 --> 2:10:09.426
-[Paul] Upsy-daisy.
-[grunts]

2:10:12.679 --> 2:10:14.306
[engine starting]

2:10:16.934 --> 2:10:18.060
John,

2:10:18.602 --> 2:10:20.187
do you know where
we're taking you tonight?

2:10:23.941 --> 2:10:25.108
Help a lady?

2:10:27.319 --> 2:10:28.529
[Brutal] That's right.

2:10:29.738 --> 2:10:30.781
But how do you know?

2:10:32.574 --> 2:10:33.951
Don't know.

2:10:35.911 --> 2:10:37.079
Tell the truth, boss,

2:10:38.038 --> 2:10:39.623
I don't know much of anything.

2:10:41.708 --> 2:10:42.960
I never have.

2:10:45.754 --> 2:10:47.005
[knocks]

2:11:11.196 --> 2:11:12.698
[engine stops]

2:11:18.287 --> 2:11:19.830
We can still turn back.

2:11:22.124 --> 2:11:24.793
Boss, look. Someone's up.

2:11:24.877 --> 2:11:26.086
[sighs]

2:11:26.962 --> 2:11:28.338
This was a mistake.

2:11:29.256 --> 2:11:31.341
Oh, Christ, Paul, what were we thinking?

2:11:31.425 --> 2:11:33.844
It's too late now. John, you stay.

2:11:38.891 --> 2:11:41.476
Harry, you keep John here
till we call you.

2:11:52.112 --> 2:11:54.740
Who the hell goes there at 2:30
in the goddamn morning?

2:11:54.823 --> 2:11:56.950
[stammering] Hal, it's us.
It's Paul and Brutal.

2:11:57.409 --> 2:11:58.994
-It's us.
-Jesus.

2:11:59.077 --> 2:12:01.580
It isn't a lockdown, is it? Or a riot?

2:12:01.663 --> 2:12:05.125
[Paul] No. Hal, for God's sakes,
just take your finger off the trigger.

2:12:05.208 --> 2:12:06.335
[Hal] Are you hostages?

2:12:07.502 --> 2:12:09.212
Who's out there?

2:12:09.296 --> 2:12:11.381
-Who's by that truck?
-Harry, the lights!

2:12:15.677 --> 2:12:17.095
John Coffey.

2:12:18.096 --> 2:12:19.389
-Halt!
-[Paul] Hal.

2:12:19.473 --> 2:12:22.059
-[Hal] You stay right where you are!
-[Paul] Relax, now. Take it easy, now.

2:12:22.142 --> 2:12:23.727
-[Hal] Don't you move!
-Wait!

2:12:23.810 --> 2:12:25.020
-[Hal] I'm warning you.
-John, wait!

2:12:25.103 --> 2:12:27.147
-[Paul] Hal, listen!
-Halt right there or I'll shoot!

2:12:27.230 --> 2:12:28.941
-[Hal] I said, halt!
-[Paul] Hal, put the gun down!

2:12:29.024 --> 2:12:30.150
-Halt!
-Hal.

2:12:30.233 --> 2:12:31.443
[Melinda] Hal!

2:12:33.528 --> 2:12:34.571
Hal!

2:12:34.905 --> 2:12:37.157
Who you talking to down there?

2:12:37.699 --> 2:12:39.034
God damn it!

2:12:39.117 --> 2:12:41.119
Hal, now, nobody is hurt.

2:12:42.245 --> 2:12:43.455
And we are here to help.

2:12:43.538 --> 2:12:44.873
Help what?

2:12:45.624 --> 2:12:46.833
I don't understand.

2:12:46.917 --> 2:12:49.336
-You're just gonna have to trust me.
-[Melinda sobbing]

2:13:06.478 --> 2:13:07.604
What do you want?

2:13:08.063 --> 2:13:09.523
[Melinda] Hal!

2:13:10.607 --> 2:13:12.609
Make them go away!

2:13:13.610 --> 2:13:16.279
I don't want no salesmen

2:13:17.030 --> 2:13:19.116
in the middle of the night.

2:13:19.908 --> 2:13:23.912
Tell them to take
a flying fuck at a rolling...

2:13:23.996 --> 2:13:25.288
[Coffey] Just to help.

2:13:25.872 --> 2:13:28.250
Just to help, boss. That's all.

2:13:29.418 --> 2:13:30.752
You can't.

2:13:31.420 --> 2:13:32.587
No one can.

2:13:38.844 --> 2:13:40.929
[Melinda continues sobbing]

2:13:44.057 --> 2:13:46.435
-[Melinda] Stay out of here!
-Don't you go in there!

2:13:46.768 --> 2:13:49.229
[Melinda] Whoever you are, just stay out!
[Hal] Don't you do it!

2:13:50.230 --> 2:13:52.649
[Melinda] I'm not dressed for visitors.

2:13:54.568 --> 2:13:56.945
You stop now. You hear me?

2:13:57.696 --> 2:13:59.364
Paul, I don't want him up there.

2:13:59.448 --> 2:14:02.242
Boss, you just be quiet now.

2:14:04.786 --> 2:14:06.913
[Melinda moans]

2:14:50.832 --> 2:14:53.251
It's all right, Hal. It's all right.

2:14:53.335 --> 2:14:55.629
[whispering] Hal, watch. Just watch him.

2:15:02.010 --> 2:15:04.554
Don't come near me, pig fucker.

2:15:18.527 --> 2:15:21.404
Why do you have so many scars?

2:15:23.698 --> 2:15:26.409
Who hurt you so badly, huh?

2:15:27.536 --> 2:15:29.704
Don't hardly remember, ma'am.

2:15:32.415 --> 2:15:34.376
What's your name, huh?

2:15:34.459 --> 2:15:37.295
John Coffey, ma'am. Like the drink.

2:15:38.171 --> 2:15:40.132
Only not spelt the same.

2:15:47.180 --> 2:15:48.348
Ma'am?

2:15:48.849 --> 2:15:50.559
[breathing heavily]

2:15:56.106 --> 2:15:58.233
[hoarsely] Yes, John Coffey?

2:15:59.860 --> 2:16:01.111
I see it.

2:16:02.112 --> 2:16:03.405
-[sobbing]
-I see it.

2:16:10.579 --> 2:16:12.831
What's happening?

2:16:13.999 --> 2:16:19.087
Shh, you be still now.
You be so quiet and so still.

2:16:47.199 --> 2:16:49.159
[inhaling]

2:16:53.413 --> 2:16:54.748
[rumbling]

2:16:59.794 --> 2:17:01.046
[ticking]

2:17:07.219 --> 2:17:08.762
[loud rumbling]

2:17:34.329 --> 2:17:36.164
[coughing]

2:17:45.507 --> 2:17:47.842
Come on, John. Sick it up.

2:17:47.926 --> 2:17:50.345
[patting] Come on.
Cough it out like you done before.

2:17:51.972 --> 2:17:55.600
He's choking. Whatever he sucked
out of her, he's choking on it.

2:17:56.309 --> 2:17:57.394
John.

2:17:59.062 --> 2:18:01.606
I'll be fine. Just let me be.

2:18:15.203 --> 2:18:16.496
[hoarsely] How did I get here?

2:18:19.291 --> 2:18:24.045
We... We were going
to the hospital in Vicksburg.

2:18:24.587 --> 2:18:28.049
-Remember?
-Shh... [sniffles] Melly.

2:18:28.800 --> 2:18:33.096
It doesn't matter.
It doesn't matter anymore.

2:18:33.179 --> 2:18:34.973
Did I have the X-ray?

2:18:36.266 --> 2:18:37.434
Did I?

2:18:40.562 --> 2:18:41.896
[Paul] Yes.

2:18:42.689 --> 2:18:45.442
Yes. It was clear.

2:18:45.525 --> 2:18:46.776
There was no tumor.

2:18:46.860 --> 2:18:48.445
[sobbing]

2:18:51.614 --> 2:18:52.657
Oh.

2:18:53.950 --> 2:18:55.577
[whispering] Hal.

2:19:02.751 --> 2:19:07.380
John, can you stand up?
Can you turn around and see this lady?

2:19:09.049 --> 2:19:10.383
[grunting]

2:19:14.596 --> 2:19:16.348
[coughing]

2:19:20.435 --> 2:19:22.062
What's your name?

2:19:23.438 --> 2:19:25.148
John Coffey, ma'am.

2:19:26.858 --> 2:19:28.401
Like the drink.

2:19:30.028 --> 2:19:31.988
Only not spelt the same.

2:19:32.530 --> 2:19:35.784
No, ma'am, not spelt the same at all.

2:19:39.204 --> 2:19:41.956
Melly. No, you can't.

2:20:07.148 --> 2:20:08.817
I dreamed of you.

2:20:12.070 --> 2:20:14.864
I dreamed you were wandering in the dark.

2:20:16.324 --> 2:20:17.826
And so was I.

2:20:20.036 --> 2:20:22.163
And we found each other.

2:20:23.331 --> 2:20:25.834
We found each other in the dark.

2:20:45.437 --> 2:20:47.021
Take it, John. It's a present.

2:20:47.605 --> 2:20:49.399
It's St. Christopher.

2:20:50.859 --> 2:20:52.986
I want you to have it, Mr. Coffey.

2:20:54.028 --> 2:20:56.072
And wear it. He'll keep you safe.

2:20:56.865 --> 2:21:00.034
Please. Wear it for me.

2:21:11.212 --> 2:21:12.547
[coughing]

2:21:15.467 --> 2:21:16.759
[hoarsely] Thank you, ma'am.

2:21:18.803 --> 2:21:20.388
Thank you, John.

2:21:27.645 --> 2:21:29.689
Christ, he goes down,

2:21:29.772 --> 2:21:31.900
it'll take three mules and a crane
to pick him up again.

2:21:32.358 --> 2:21:35.653
Take it easy, John. Come on, now.
You gotta stay on your feet.

2:21:35.737 --> 2:21:37.071
[coughing]

2:21:51.753 --> 2:21:54.422
He'll never sit in Old Sparky.
You know that, don't you?

2:21:55.381 --> 2:21:57.592
He swallowed that stuff for a reason.

2:21:58.259 --> 2:22:00.678
I give him a few days.

2:22:00.762 --> 2:22:03.223
One of us will be doing a cell check,
and there he'll be,

2:22:03.306 --> 2:22:04.516
dead on his bunk.

2:22:04.599 --> 2:22:07.185
Well, if that's his choice,
he's earned it.

2:22:07.268 --> 2:22:09.145
Let's just get him back on the Mile.

2:22:12.565 --> 2:22:14.526
[Coffey coughing]

2:22:15.109 --> 2:22:16.444
[grunting]

2:22:20.907 --> 2:22:23.243
[breathing heavily]

2:22:23.326 --> 2:22:25.203
Oh, boy, am I happy to see you fellows.

2:22:25.286 --> 2:22:28.414
You were gone so long, Wild Bill's making
noise like he's gonna wake up.

2:22:28.498 --> 2:22:29.499
What the hell happened to him?

2:22:29.832 --> 2:22:32.460
He's hurting, Dean. He's hurting bad.

2:22:36.381 --> 2:22:38.299
Okay, John.

2:22:38.383 --> 2:22:41.844
We gonna set you down on your bed now.

2:22:41.928 --> 2:22:43.263
Here we go.

2:22:43.346 --> 2:22:45.139
[continues coughing]

2:23:01.406 --> 2:23:02.490
Well?

2:23:04.534 --> 2:23:06.452
What about Mrs. Moores?

2:23:08.580 --> 2:23:10.456
Was it like the mouse?

2:23:11.666 --> 2:23:12.959
Was it,

2:23:14.877 --> 2:23:17.338
you know, a miracle?

2:23:17.922 --> 2:23:19.132
Yes.

2:23:20.466 --> 2:23:22.218
Yes, it was.

2:23:23.261 --> 2:23:24.429
Damn.

2:23:24.971 --> 2:23:26.472
[door opening]

2:23:40.069 --> 2:23:41.321
Now,

2:23:41.863 --> 2:23:44.782
I want to talk, not shout.

2:23:44.866 --> 2:23:47.577
I take that tape off, you gonna be calm?

2:23:47.660 --> 2:23:48.870
Mmm-hmm.

2:23:50.580 --> 2:23:53.374
My mother always says you do it fast,
it won't hurt so much.

2:23:53.875 --> 2:23:55.835
[muffled protest]

2:23:57.211 --> 2:23:58.963
Guess she was wrong.

2:24:00.340 --> 2:24:01.549
[coughs]

2:24:02.383 --> 2:24:03.801
Let me out of this nut-coat.

2:24:03.885 --> 2:24:06.179
-In a minute.
-Now! Right now!

2:24:06.262 --> 2:24:08.806
I want out now... [exclaims]

2:24:10.475 --> 2:24:11.684
[grunts]

2:24:11.768 --> 2:24:13.519
Shut up and listen.

2:24:14.729 --> 2:24:17.106
Now you deserved to be punished
for what you did to Del.

2:24:17.190 --> 2:24:18.358
You accept it like a man.

2:24:19.233 --> 2:24:21.319
Or else we'll make you sorry
you were ever born.

2:24:22.195 --> 2:24:25.323
We'll tell people
how you sabotaged Del's execution...

2:24:25.406 --> 2:24:26.741
Sabotaged?

2:24:26.824 --> 2:24:28.743
How you pissed yourself
like a frightened little girl.

2:24:28.826 --> 2:24:31.037
Ooh, yes. Yeah, we will talk.

2:24:32.288 --> 2:24:33.748
But, Percy,

2:24:34.248 --> 2:24:35.917
you mind me, now.

2:24:36.918 --> 2:24:40.380
We'll also see you beaten
within an inch of your life.

2:24:42.423 --> 2:24:43.675
We know people, too.

2:24:45.259 --> 2:24:47.428
Are you so foolish,
you don't realize that?

2:24:49.972 --> 2:24:52.767
Let bygones be bygones, hmm?

2:24:54.143 --> 2:24:57.063
Nothing's hurt so far but your pride.

2:24:57.146 --> 2:25:01.234
No one ever need know about that,
except the people in this little room.

2:25:01.776 --> 2:25:04.654
What happens on the Mile
stays on the Mile.

2:25:06.239 --> 2:25:07.615
Always has.

2:25:12.120 --> 2:25:13.496
Hmm.

2:25:16.916 --> 2:25:19.335
May I be let out of this coat now?

2:25:39.272 --> 2:25:40.356
My things?

2:25:43.609 --> 2:25:45.403
Think it over, Percy.

2:25:46.487 --> 2:25:48.114
Oh, I intend to.

2:25:49.282 --> 2:25:52.160
I intend to think it over very hard.

2:25:53.911 --> 2:25:55.663
Starting right now.

2:26:05.548 --> 2:26:08.676
He'll talk. Sooner or later.

2:26:09.177 --> 2:26:10.261
Hmm.

2:26:18.644 --> 2:26:19.854
[gasps]

2:26:23.316 --> 2:26:25.651
-Hey, let him go!
-John, let go!

2:26:25.735 --> 2:26:28.571
-Let go, John!
-John, God damn it! Let him go!

2:26:28.654 --> 2:26:29.781
Let go, John! No!

2:26:29.864 --> 2:26:31.115
[screaming]

2:26:31.199 --> 2:26:32.742
