2:26:33.743 --> 2:26:36.287
John, stop it! Stop it, John!

2:26:36.370 --> 2:26:38.456
-Let him go! Back off!
-John, let him go!

2:26:40.541 --> 2:26:41.793
[gagging]

2:27:02.230 --> 2:27:03.898
[exhaling]

2:27:13.866 --> 2:27:15.076
[gasps]

2:27:34.887 --> 2:27:36.097
[grunts]

2:27:39.267 --> 2:27:41.811
Easy, now. Easy.

2:27:43.604 --> 2:27:44.939
Easy. Hey.

2:27:46.107 --> 2:27:47.149
Hey.

2:27:51.237 --> 2:27:52.405
Percy.

2:27:55.533 --> 2:27:57.201
Are you all right?

2:28:29.817 --> 2:28:31.485
Boy, what you looking at?

2:28:39.619 --> 2:28:43.247
What you looking at? You limp noodle.

2:28:43.789 --> 2:28:45.625
You wanna kiss my ass?

2:28:46.459 --> 2:28:47.877
You wanna suck my dick?

2:28:55.885 --> 2:28:56.886
[holster opening]

2:28:58.471 --> 2:28:59.889
[gunshots]

2:28:59.972 --> 2:29:01.098
[all] No!

2:29:01.807 --> 2:29:03.392
-[indistinct shouting]
-[gasps]

2:29:09.106 --> 2:29:11.150
Grab the gun! Dean, grab the gun!

2:29:13.945 --> 2:29:15.196
[gasping]

2:29:17.531 --> 2:29:18.658
[Dean] Oh, no.

2:29:19.659 --> 2:29:21.327
No, no, no.

2:29:22.078 --> 2:29:23.746
-Oh, no.
-[gasping]

2:30:14.005 --> 2:30:16.215
I punished them bad men.

2:30:17.008 --> 2:30:18.676
I punished them both.

2:30:19.051 --> 2:30:20.261
Why?

2:30:21.220 --> 2:30:22.346
Why Wild Bill?

2:30:23.764 --> 2:30:27.309
I saw in his heart when he grabbed my arm.

2:30:28.936 --> 2:30:30.730
I saw what Wild Billy done.

2:30:31.605 --> 2:30:33.399
Saw it plain as day.

2:30:34.942 --> 2:30:37.486
You can't hide what's in your heart.

2:30:38.029 --> 2:30:39.196
What?

2:30:40.906 --> 2:30:42.241
You saw what?

2:30:46.245 --> 2:30:47.997
Take my hand, boss.

2:30:51.459 --> 2:30:52.918
You see for yourself.

2:30:55.046 --> 2:30:57.590
Paul, no.

2:31:02.094 --> 2:31:03.304
Please.

2:31:09.560 --> 2:31:10.770
[grunts]

2:31:11.812 --> 2:31:13.814
No, no, no.

2:31:14.774 --> 2:31:17.526
-Please.
-I gots to, boss.

2:31:17.610 --> 2:31:20.112
I gots to give you a little bit of myself.

2:31:21.864 --> 2:31:23.866
-A gift.
-[girls laughing]

2:31:24.617 --> 2:31:28.621
A gift of what's inside of me
so you can see for yourself.

2:31:31.874 --> 2:31:33.084
[girls singing]

2:31:41.967 --> 2:31:43.677
[inaudible]

2:31:50.518 --> 2:31:53.104
Hot cross buns with warm milk.

2:32:01.028 --> 2:32:02.655
[girls continue singing]

2:32:22.758 --> 2:32:24.009
[Marjorie] Klaus!

2:32:26.554 --> 2:32:29.682
Suppertime! Bring the girls.

2:32:33.853 --> 2:32:36.272
Girls! You heard your mama!

2:32:37.565 --> 2:32:40.151
[squealing] Yes, papa! We're coming!

2:32:40.234 --> 2:32:42.194
[giggling]

2:32:55.875 --> 2:32:57.793
[sobbing]

2:32:58.711 --> 2:33:01.839
Come on, Billy.
I worked you enough for one day.

2:33:02.631 --> 2:33:04.633
Come get you some supper.

2:33:07.303 --> 2:33:11.682
[girls] God is great, God is good,
and we thank you...

2:33:30.743 --> 2:33:32.077
[creaking]

2:33:36.040 --> 2:33:37.833
[Wharton whispering]<i> You love your sister?</i>

2:33:37.917 --> 2:33:40.127
<i>You make any noise, you know what happens?</i>

2:33:40.753 --> 2:33:43.172
I'm gonna kill her instead of you.

2:33:43.255 --> 2:33:46.717
You make any noise, I'm gonna kill her.
You understand?

2:33:46.800 --> 2:33:48.344
You understand?

2:33:48.928 --> 2:33:50.429
Shh!

2:33:51.305 --> 2:33:52.640
[grunting]

2:33:56.769 --> 2:33:58.103
[coughing]

2:34:00.189 --> 2:34:01.440
[panting]

2:34:04.401 --> 2:34:05.653
[sobbing]

2:34:06.987 --> 2:34:10.866
He killed them with they love,
they love for each other.

2:34:12.409 --> 2:34:14.286
Now you see how it is.

2:34:15.913 --> 2:34:18.207
That's the way it is every day.

2:34:19.124 --> 2:34:22.836
That's the way it is all over the world.

2:34:27.424 --> 2:34:29.134
[breathing heavily]

2:34:33.472 --> 2:34:35.224
[man 1] Percy.
[man 2] Percy Wetmore.

2:34:35.307 --> 2:34:36.725
-[man] Percy.
-[men speaking indistinctly]

2:34:36.809 --> 2:34:39.895
-[man 1] Son?
-Percy. Percy Wetmore.

2:34:41.021 --> 2:34:42.106
Son?

2:34:42.815 --> 2:34:44.441
Son, can you hear me?

2:34:44.525 --> 2:34:45.818
Speak up if you can hear us.

2:34:46.819 --> 2:34:49.613
I think this boy's cheese
slid off his cracker.

2:34:49.947 --> 2:34:51.615
[men speaking indistinctly]

2:34:51.699 --> 2:34:54.910
[man 2] Percy,
I got to ask you a few questions.

2:34:54.994 --> 2:34:58.205
[Dean] That's right. One minute,
he was fine, and the next, blammo.

2:34:58.289 --> 2:35:00.708
[Brutal] Dirty bastard grabbed him
through the bars few days back.

2:35:00.791 --> 2:35:02.793
Scared the boy so bad, he wet hisself.

2:35:04.461 --> 2:35:07.214
See, we didn't even...
We didn't see it happen.

2:35:07.298 --> 2:35:09.008
[continue speaking indistinctly]

2:35:11.385 --> 2:35:16.515
I'll cover for you as much as I can,
even if it means my job.

2:35:17.766 --> 2:35:19.518
But I have to know,

2:35:20.144 --> 2:35:22.938
does this have anything to do
with what happened at my house?

2:35:26.191 --> 2:35:27.693
Does it, Paul?

2:35:29.695 --> 2:35:30.738
No.

2:36:06.106 --> 2:36:08.317
[soft music playing on radio]

2:36:35.511 --> 2:36:37.012
[clicks tongue]

2:36:37.096 --> 2:36:38.305
[sighs]

2:36:55.155 --> 2:36:56.448
[turns radio off]

2:36:58.367 --> 2:37:01.703
Does Hal know?
That Coffey's innocent, I mean.

2:37:03.455 --> 2:37:05.124
Well, can he help?

2:37:05.666 --> 2:37:08.293
Does he have the influence
to do something about this?

2:37:08.836 --> 2:37:10.254
Stop the execution?

2:37:10.337 --> 2:37:11.380
No.

2:37:14.675 --> 2:37:16.635
Then don't tell him.

2:37:16.718 --> 2:37:18.804
If it can't help, don't tell him.

2:37:19.471 --> 2:37:20.556
Ever.

2:37:22.933 --> 2:37:24.476
I won't.

2:37:34.486 --> 2:37:36.029
[sighs]

2:37:36.113 --> 2:37:38.490
There's no way out of this
for you, is there?

2:37:40.284 --> 2:37:41.326
No.

2:37:42.411 --> 2:37:44.997
And I've been thinking about it,
believe me.

2:37:45.080 --> 2:37:48.292
I've been running it through my head
any number of ways.

2:37:48.834 --> 2:37:49.835
No.

2:37:51.128 --> 2:37:52.838
I'll tell you the truth, honey.

2:37:54.715 --> 2:37:58.886
I've done some things in my life
that I am not proud of,

2:38:00.095 --> 2:38:04.266
but this is the first time I've ever felt
real danger of hell.

2:38:06.185 --> 2:38:07.269
Hell?

2:38:09.021 --> 2:38:10.439
[whispers] Oh, Paul.

2:38:13.192 --> 2:38:14.568
Talk to him.

2:38:16.028 --> 2:38:17.488
Talk to John.

2:38:19.656 --> 2:38:21.533
Find out what he wants.

2:38:25.537 --> 2:38:27.456
[footsteps approaching]

2:38:27.539 --> 2:38:29.041
[keys jangling]

2:38:30.250 --> 2:38:32.002
[cell door opening]

2:38:38.550 --> 2:38:39.635
Hello, boss.

2:38:40.594 --> 2:38:42.012
Hello, John.

2:38:43.388 --> 2:38:45.682
I guess you know
we're coming down to it now.

2:38:46.642 --> 2:38:48.227
Another couple of days.

2:39:01.782 --> 2:39:04.326
Is there anything special
you wanna eat for dinner that night?

2:39:05.285 --> 2:39:07.162
We can rustle you up most anything.

2:39:17.631 --> 2:39:19.633
Meat loaf be nice.

2:39:19.716 --> 2:39:23.595
Mashed taters, gravy. Okra.

2:39:25.264 --> 2:39:28.016
Maybe some of that fine corn bread
your missus make.

2:39:28.850 --> 2:39:30.769
If she don't mind.

2:39:33.146 --> 2:39:34.481
Now, uh...

2:39:35.190 --> 2:39:39.528
What about a preacher?
Someone to say a little prayer with.

2:39:40.237 --> 2:39:42.114
Don't want no preacher.

2:39:43.532 --> 2:39:45.951
You can say a prayer, if you like.

2:39:46.785 --> 2:39:48.120
Me?

2:39:50.872 --> 2:39:53.417
Suppose I could, if it came to that.

2:39:57.671 --> 2:39:58.797
John,

2:40:01.758 --> 2:40:04.469
I have to ask you
something very important now.

2:40:06.346 --> 2:40:08.390
I know what you gonna say.

2:40:09.016 --> 2:40:10.392
You don't have to say it.

2:40:10.851 --> 2:40:13.604
No, I do. I do. I have to say it.

2:40:15.105 --> 2:40:16.523
John,

2:40:18.233 --> 2:40:20.360
tell me what you want me to do.

2:40:21.445 --> 2:40:23.280
You want me to take you out of here?

2:40:24.615 --> 2:40:26.658
Just let you run away?

2:40:26.742 --> 2:40:28.452
See how far you could get?

2:40:30.203 --> 2:40:32.497
Why would you do such a foolish thing?

2:40:34.916 --> 2:40:37.461
On the day of my judgment,

2:40:37.544 --> 2:40:40.047
when I stand before God

2:40:40.130 --> 2:40:43.425
and he asks me why did I...

2:40:44.301 --> 2:40:48.680
Did I kill one of his true miracles,

2:40:50.307 --> 2:40:52.184
what am I going to say?

2:40:53.393 --> 2:40:55.145
That it was my job?

2:40:57.606 --> 2:40:59.024
It's my job.

2:40:59.691 --> 2:41:03.695
You tell God the Father
it was a kindness you done.

2:41:07.532 --> 2:41:09.701
I know you're hurting and worrying.

2:41:10.702 --> 2:41:14.122
I can feel it on you.
But you ought to quit on it now.

2:41:15.457 --> 2:41:17.959
I want it to be over and done with.

2:41:19.211 --> 2:41:20.337
I do.

2:41:22.047 --> 2:41:23.215
[sighs]

2:41:25.258 --> 2:41:26.885
I'm tired, boss.

2:41:28.387 --> 2:41:32.391
I'm tired of being on the road,
lonely as a sparrow in the rain.

2:41:34.142 --> 2:41:36.895
I'm tired of never having me
a buddy to be with,

2:41:37.521 --> 2:41:41.441
to tell me where we's going to,
coming from, or why.

2:41:42.984 --> 2:41:46.697
Mostly, I'm tired of people
being ugly to each other.

2:41:48.115 --> 2:41:51.910
I'm tired of all the pain
I feel and hear in the world,

2:41:52.577 --> 2:41:53.912
every day.

2:41:54.413 --> 2:41:56.331
There's too much of it.

2:41:56.873 --> 2:41:59.960
It's like pieces of glass in my head,

2:42:00.794 --> 2:42:02.254
all the time.

2:42:04.798 --> 2:42:06.550
Can you understand?

2:42:09.553 --> 2:42:12.180
Yes, John, I think I can.

2:42:15.016 --> 2:42:17.227
[Brutal] Well, there must be something
we can do for you, John.

2:42:20.605 --> 2:42:22.441
There must be something that you want.

2:42:32.200 --> 2:42:35.746
I ain't never seen me a flicker show.

2:42:37.789 --> 2:42:39.458
[man singing on screen]

2:42:39.541 --> 2:42:41.501
<i>I'm in heaven</i>

2:42:42.627 --> 2:42:48.175
<i>And my heart beats</i>
<i>so that I can hardly speak</i>

2:42:49.342 --> 2:42:54.931
<i>And I seem to find the happiness I seek</i>

2:42:55.724 --> 2:43:01.062
<i>When we're out together dancing</i>
<i>cheek to cheek</i>

2:44:02.374 --> 2:44:04.459
Why, they's angels.

2:44:05.752 --> 2:44:08.380
Angels, just like up in heaven.

2:44:08.463 --> 2:44:10.090
[music continues]

2:44:27.065 --> 2:44:28.942
[keys jangling]

2:45:09.107 --> 2:45:11.067
It be all right, fellas.

2:45:12.527 --> 2:45:14.571
This here's the hard part.

2:45:16.072 --> 2:45:17.532
I'll be all right in a little while.

2:45:18.533 --> 2:45:22.787
John, I should have this just for now.

2:45:27.292 --> 2:45:29.294
I'll give it back after.

2:45:32.631 --> 2:45:36.885
You know, I fell asleep this afternoon
and had me a dream.

2:45:38.720 --> 2:45:40.513
I dreamed about Del's mouse.

2:45:41.973 --> 2:45:43.016
Did you, John?

2:45:43.683 --> 2:45:48.396
I dreamed Mr. Jingles got down
to that place Boss Howell talked about.

2:45:48.480 --> 2:45:50.315
That Mouseville place.

2:45:51.107 --> 2:45:53.276
I dreamed there's kids.
[laughs]

2:45:54.027 --> 2:45:57.781
And how they laughed at his tricks. My!
[continues laughing]

2:45:59.699 --> 2:46:03.161
I dreamed that those two little
blond-headed girls was there.

2:46:03.870 --> 2:46:05.914
They's laughing, too.

2:46:05.997 --> 2:46:09.250
I put my arms around them
and set 'em on my knees.

2:46:09.334 --> 2:46:13.421
And there's no blood coming out
of they hair, and they's just fine.

2:46:13.505 --> 2:46:16.675
We all watched Mr. Jingles
roll that spool.

2:46:18.176 --> 2:46:19.427
How we did laugh.

2:46:19.511 --> 2:46:21.304
Fit to bust, we was!

2:46:37.445 --> 2:46:38.530
John.

2:46:39.739 --> 2:46:43.952
[whispering] They's lots of folks here
that hate me. Lots!

2:46:45.745 --> 2:46:47.247
I can feel it.

2:46:47.998 --> 2:46:49.874
It's like bees stinging me.

2:46:50.291 --> 2:46:52.502
Well, feel how we feel, then.

2:46:54.004 --> 2:46:55.046
We don't hate you.

2:46:56.631 --> 2:46:58.049
Can you feel that?

2:47:00.385 --> 2:47:02.345
[Klaus] Kill him twice, you boys!

2:47:03.263 --> 2:47:07.434
You go on and kill
that raping baby killer twice!

2:47:07.517 --> 2:47:09.060
That'd be fine!

2:47:25.869 --> 2:47:28.329
Wipe your face before you stand up, Dean.

2:47:28.747 --> 2:47:29.998
Yes, sir.

2:47:30.749 --> 2:47:32.083
[sniffles]

2:47:32.751 --> 2:47:33.918
[sighs]

2:47:42.093 --> 2:47:43.261
Roll on one.

2:47:47.348 --> 2:47:49.017
[machine whirring]

2:47:51.269 --> 2:47:54.689
[Marjorie] Does it hurt yet?
I hope it does.

2:47:55.648 --> 2:47:57.692
I hope it hurts like hell.

2:47:59.944 --> 2:48:01.863
John Coffey, you've been condemned to die

2:48:01.946 --> 2:48:03.948
in the electric chair
by a jury of your peers,

2:48:04.032 --> 2:48:07.827
sentence imposed by a judge
in good standing in this state.

2:48:07.911 --> 2:48:10.663
Do you have anything to say
before sentence is carried out?

2:48:12.957 --> 2:48:14.918
I'm sorry for what I am.

2:48:27.514 --> 2:48:28.973
Please, boss,

2:48:30.558 --> 2:48:32.977
don't put that thing over my face.

2:48:34.479 --> 2:48:36.481
Don't put me in the dark.

2:48:37.482 --> 2:48:39.692
[whispering] I's afraid of the dark.

2:48:49.828 --> 2:48:51.162
[softly] All right, John.

2:49:11.558 --> 2:49:14.602
[singing softly]
<i>Heaven, I'm in heaven</i>

2:49:14.686 --> 2:49:17.647
<i>Heaven, heaven</i>

2:49:17.730 --> 2:49:19.524
<i>I'm in heaven</i>

2:49:20.024 --> 2:49:20.859
[whispering]

2:49:20.942 --> 2:49:22.610
<i>Heaven, heaven</i>

2:49:23.153 --> 2:49:24.612
<i>I'm in heaven</i>

2:49:25.155 --> 2:49:26.656
<i>Heaven</i>

2:49:27.615 --> 2:49:30.076
<i>Heaven, I'm in heaven</i>

2:49:30.702 --> 2:49:32.453
<i>I'm in heaven</i>

2:49:32.537 --> 2:49:34.205
<i>I'm in heaven</i>

2:49:34.289 --> 2:49:35.832
<i>I'm in heaven</i>

2:49:36.666 --> 2:49:37.792
<i>Heaven</i>

2:49:37.876 --> 2:49:39.127
<i>Heaven</i>

2:49:39.836 --> 2:49:40.879
<i>Heaven</i>

2:49:45.717 --> 2:49:47.093
John Coffey,

2:49:48.219 --> 2:49:51.514
electricity shall now be passed
through your body until you are dead

2:49:51.598 --> 2:49:53.474
in accordance with state law.

2:49:56.144 --> 2:49:59.397
May God have mercy on your soul.

2:50:34.349 --> 2:50:35.391
[whispering] Paul.

2:50:38.603 --> 2:50:40.313
You have to say it.

2:50:42.190 --> 2:50:44.275
You have to give the order.

2:51:02.585 --> 2:51:04.879
[John] <i>He killed 'em with they love.</i>

2:51:04.963 --> 2:51:09.008
<i>That's how it is every day</i>
<i>all over the world.</i>

2:51:23.564 --> 2:51:25.108
[shakily] Roll on two.

2:51:26.651 --> 2:51:28.194
[electricity sizzling]

2:53:09.754 --> 2:53:12.423
[Paul] <i>It was the last execution</i>
<i>I ever took part in.</i>

2:53:13.257 --> 2:53:15.885
I just couldn't do it anymore after that.

2:53:15.968 --> 2:53:21.933
Brutal either. We both transferred out,
took jobs with Boys' Correctional.

2:53:23.101 --> 2:53:24.769
It was all right.

2:53:25.603 --> 2:53:28.106
"Catch them young" became my motto.

2:53:31.651 --> 2:53:32.944
You don't believe me.

2:53:33.778 --> 2:53:36.406
I don't imagine you'd lie to me, Paul.

2:53:37.031 --> 2:53:39.409
-It's just that--
-It's quite a story.

2:53:39.492 --> 2:53:41.244
It's quite a story.

2:53:42.120 --> 2:53:44.539
One thing I don't understand.

2:53:44.622 --> 2:53:49.836
You said you and Jan
had a grown son in 1935.

2:53:50.461 --> 2:53:51.963
Is that right?

2:53:52.422 --> 2:53:54.382
The math doesn't work, does it?

2:54:00.012 --> 2:54:02.348
Do you feel up to taking a walk?

2:54:03.057 --> 2:54:04.642
[birds chirping]

2:54:23.286 --> 2:54:24.495
[Paul] Watch your step.

2:54:25.288 --> 2:54:27.290
Now let your eyes adjust.

2:54:39.427 --> 2:54:40.595
There.

2:54:43.097 --> 2:54:46.934
Hey. Wake up, old fella. Wake up.

2:54:50.938 --> 2:54:54.692
Paul, it isn't. It can't be.

2:54:59.197 --> 2:55:00.615
Come over here, boy.

2:55:01.199 --> 2:55:03.409
Come on over here and see this lady.

2:55:06.412 --> 2:55:09.081
That can't be Mr. Jingles.

2:55:15.213 --> 2:55:17.006
[speaking in French]

2:55:32.063 --> 2:55:33.981
Go on, you can do it.

2:55:41.656 --> 2:55:45.535
This isn't exactly the Mouseville
we had in mind, is it?

2:55:46.953 --> 2:55:50.248
But we make do. Don't we, old fella?

2:55:57.380 --> 2:56:00.258
I think Mr. Jingles happened by accident.

2:56:01.551 --> 2:56:05.930
I think when we electrocuted Del,
and it all went so badly,

2:56:06.472 --> 2:56:08.766
well, John could feel that, you know.

2:56:09.267 --> 2:56:11.811
And I think a part of

2:56:12.937 --> 2:56:15.565
whatever magic was inside of him

2:56:15.648 --> 2:56:18.359
just leapt into my tiny friend here.

2:56:20.236 --> 2:56:21.821
As for me,

2:56:23.281 --> 2:56:25.783
John had to give me a part of himself,

2:56:26.284 --> 2:56:28.578
a gift, the way he saw it,

2:56:28.661 --> 2:56:31.622
so that I could see for myself
what Wild Bill had done.

2:56:34.542 --> 2:56:36.294
When John did that,

2:56:38.296 --> 2:56:40.131
when he took my hand,

2:56:41.632 --> 2:56:43.342
a part of the power

2:56:43.968 --> 2:56:45.553
that worked through him

2:56:46.345 --> 2:56:47.972
spilled into me.

2:56:48.806 --> 2:56:50.016
He what?

2:56:50.891 --> 2:56:54.478
He infected you with life?

2:56:56.022 --> 2:56:58.149
It's as good a word as any.

2:56:59.817 --> 2:57:03.904
He infected us both, didn't he,
Mr. Jingles? With life.

2:57:08.618 --> 2:57:10.995
I'm 108 years old, Elaine.

2:57:11.829 --> 2:57:15.416
I was 44 the year that John Coffey
walked the Green Mile.

2:57:19.086 --> 2:57:21.005
You mustn't blame John.

2:57:21.505 --> 2:57:26.135
He couldn't help what happened.
He was... He's just a force of nature.

2:57:27.970 --> 2:57:31.766
Oh, I've lived to see
some amazing things, Ellie.

2:57:33.351 --> 2:57:35.561
Another century come to pass.

2:57:36.562 --> 2:57:37.938
But I've...

2:57:39.148 --> 2:57:43.319
I've had to see my friends
and loved ones die off through the years.

2:57:44.028 --> 2:57:45.655
Hal and Melinda,

2:57:46.489 --> 2:57:47.948
Brutus Howell,

2:57:48.032 --> 2:57:50.284
my wife, my boy.

2:57:53.704 --> 2:57:55.331
And you, Elaine.

2:57:56.666 --> 2:57:58.250
You'll die, too.

2:57:59.835 --> 2:58:03.547
And my curse is knowing
that I'll be there to see it.

2:58:05.716 --> 2:58:07.843
It's my atonement, you see.

2:58:08.719 --> 2:58:10.388
It's my punishment

2:58:10.721 --> 2:58:13.265
for letting John Coffey
ride the lightning,

2:58:15.059 --> 2:58:17.269
<i>for killing a miracle of God.</i>

2:58:19.230 --> 2:58:21.649
[priest] <i>Almighty, everlasting God,</i>

2:58:22.525 --> 2:58:24.485
the source of all being and life...

2:58:25.236 --> 2:58:28.948
[Paul] <i>You'll be gone like all the others.</i>
<i>I'll have to stay.</i>

2:58:31.492 --> 2:58:34.954
<i>Oh, I'll die eventually. Of that I'm sure.</i>

2:58:36.205 --> 2:58:39.333
<i>I have no illusions of immortality.</i>

2:58:40.459 --> 2:58:42.795
<i>But I will have wished for death</i>

2:58:43.462 --> 2:58:45.589
<i>long before death finds me.</i>

2:58:47.216 --> 2:58:50.177
<i>In truth, I wish for it already.</i>

2:58:50.261 --> 2:58:52.471
[soft music playing on radio]

2:58:56.851 --> 2:58:58.436
[soft squeaking]

2:59:03.107 --> 2:59:04.483
Mr. Jingles?

2:59:14.118 --> 2:59:15.870
Where you been, hmm?

2:59:16.579 --> 2:59:20.708
Been worried about you, boy.
You hungry, hmm?

2:59:20.791 --> 2:59:23.043
Let's go see
if we can't find you something to eat.

2:59:24.378 --> 2:59:26.130
A few crumbs anyway.

2:59:26.213 --> 2:59:28.132
I know you'd like that.

2:59:29.425 --> 2:59:31.427
Look at you. Mr. Jingles.

2:59:32.470 --> 2:59:35.723
<i>I lie in bed most nights</i>
<i>thinking about it.</i>

2:59:36.557 --> 2:59:37.933
<i>And I wait.</i>

2:59:39.185 --> 2:59:42.271
<i>I think about all the people I've loved,</i>

2:59:42.354 --> 2:59:43.856
<i>now long gone.</i>

2:59:45.316 --> 2:59:47.860
<i>I think about my beautiful Jan,</i>

2:59:47.943 --> 2:59:50.321
<i>how I lost her so many years ago.</i>

2:59:52.156 --> 2:59:57.244
<i>And I think about all of us</i>
<i>walking our own Green Mile,</i>

2:59:57.328 --> 2:59:59.163
<i>each in our own time.</i>

3:00:00.956 --> 3:00:04.084
<i>But one thought more than any other</i>

3:00:04.168 --> 3:00:06.253
<i>keeps me awake most nights.</i>

3:00:08.005 --> 3:00:11.300
<i>If he could make a mouse live so long,</i>

3:00:12.510 --> 3:00:14.553
<i>how much longer do I have?</i>

3:00:19.016 --> 3:00:21.393
<i>We each owe a death.</i>

3:00:22.061 --> 3:00:24.021
<i>There are no exceptions.</i>

3:00:25.189 --> 3:00:26.690
<i>But, oh, God,</i>

3:00:28.234 --> 3:00:29.902
<i>sometimes,</i>

3:00:30.528 --> 3:00:33.364
<i>the Green Mile seems so long.</i>
